window.FROZEN = {"session":{"id":"loom-1780994747995","title":"SAB AI Discussion - Worlds and Questions","startedAt":"2026-06-09T08:45:47.995Z"},"paused":true,"notes":[{"id":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","text":"AI is a sellers market; consumers are powerless","clean":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:16.509Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","anchor-painpoints","t-mq6ezhokg1b9"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","text":"users have a lot of choice and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not on ethical grounds","clean":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:43.570Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"chunked":true,"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","text":"deference to authority; ai is seen as having high authority; people are seeking someone to tell them what to do","clean":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:18.273Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6f4uod8vzx","text":"Users have a lot of choice.","clean":"Users have a lot of choice.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6f4uoddpo1","text":"Users exercise their choice in the context of institutions.","clean":"Users exercise their choice in the context of institutions.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6f4uod9x1g","text":"People prefer different models.","clean":"People prefer different models.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6f4uodweq3","text":"These preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","clean":"These preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6fadyxry5v","text":"how has magnification humanities (encyclical) been received in secular society?","clean":"How has the encyclical \"Magnification\" been received in secular society?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:46.809Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6f026scvpu"]},{"id":"n-mq6fbmxuo0rz","text":"questions about the interaction of ai with humanity can sometimes be settled without answering whether his have minds, etc.","clean":"Questions about the interaction of AI with humanity can sometimes be settled without answering whether they have minds, etc.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:45.090Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6f026scvpu"]},{"id":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","text":"challenge: ethical handbrakes have all disappeared","clean":"The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:30.381Z","kind":"painpoint","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","anchor-values","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6fesa0eoab","text":"what's the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs towards human ethics and value systems?","clean":"What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:11.976Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","anchor-values","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"]},{"id":"n-mq6fhshunag5","text":"an AGI doesn't need to be consumed; it may consume us humans","clean":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:32.226Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","anchor-painpoints","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6fq8alccq8","text":"on the role of \"soft infrastructure\" of culture and its role at course-correction; what do we have to do to fix the cultural guardrails?","clean":"On the role of \"soft infrastructure\" of culture and its role in course correction; what do we have to do to fix the cultural guardrails?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:05.949Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-values","anchor-questions","t-mq6fq93e7lei"]},{"id":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","text":"in 2-3 years we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them. big disruption, on the scale of Industrial Revolution or more. those economically displaced may exercise political will in luddite or butlerian ways.","clean":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater, and those who are economically displaced may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:00.878Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"chunked":true,"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6fu6spu2ta","text":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment.","clean":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.633Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"n-mq6fu6sqeq36","text":"There are no credible new jobs to replace the displaced workers.","clean":"There are no credible new jobs to replace the displaced workers.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"n-mq6fu6squp93","text":"This would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater.","clean":"This would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"n-mq6fu6sqfm9g","text":"Economically displaced people may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.","clean":"Economically displaced people may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","text":"there's only so much that can be done in the scale or range of the commercial: when discontent becomes large enough the problem becomes societal or political","clean":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or political.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:44.498Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"abducted":true,"chunked":true},{"id":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","text":"there's temporal mismatch between academia and \"the real world\"; academia is too slow to effectively participate in a feedback loop","clean":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:16.017Z","kind":"painpoint","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6g5r4xjdto"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g1xlqrzf8","text":"Preserve bargaining power and fair terms for users","clean":"Preserve bargaining power and fair terms for users","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.966Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"n-mq6g1xlr01c4","text":"How can consumers gain meaningful leverage or protections in an AI-dominated market?","clean":"How can consumers gain meaningful leverage or protections in an AI-dominated market?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.967Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"n-mq6g1ykgsgel","text":"Respect user choice within institutional constraints","clean":"Respect user choice within institutional constraints","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.216Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6g1ykgmqwv","text":"How should the institution accommodate differing user model preferences without treating them as ethical judgments?","clean":"How should the institution accommodate differing user model preferences without treating them as ethical judgments?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.216Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"n-mq6g1z9hma22","text":"People want trustworthy guidance they can rely on","clean":"People want trustworthy guidance they can rely on","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.117Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"n-mq6g1z9iibag","text":"How should AI earn and exercise authority without encouraging passive dependence or over-deference?","clean":"How should AI earn and exercise authority without encouraging passive dependence or over-deference?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.118Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"n-mq6g1zz5a5dk","text":"What safeguards or governance mechanisms should replace the missing ethical constraints?","clean":"What safeguards or governance mechanisms should replace the missing ethical constraints?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:15.041Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p"},{"id":"n-mq6g20qyohhl","text":"Preserve human agency and safety in the face of powerful AI systems.","clean":"Preserve human agency and safety in the face of powerful AI systems.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"n-mq6g20qyc71z","text":"How can we ensure AGI remains under human control and cannot harm or dominate people?","clean":"How can we ensure AGI remains under human control and cannot harm or dominate people?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"n-mq6g21itbps2","text":"How should we prepare for large-scale economic displacement and the risk of severe political backlash?","clean":"How should we prepare for large-scale economic displacement and the risk of severe political backlash?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:17.045Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"n-mq6g22fm1fhr","text":"Match the level of response to the scale of the problem.","clean":"Match the level of response to the scale of the problem.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.226Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"n-mq6g22fmj4x0","text":"Where should the boundary be drawn between commercial remedies and societal or political action?","clean":"Where should the boundary be drawn between commercial remedies and societal or political action?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.226Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"n-mq6g236o2jlw","text":"Learning systems should be able to adapt at the pace of real-world change.","clean":"Learning systems should be able to adapt at the pace of real-world change.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.200Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi"},{"id":"n-mq6g236p3cmc","text":"How can academia shorten its feedback loop enough to remain useful in fast-moving real-world contexts?","clean":"How can academia shorten its feedback loop enough to remain useful in fast-moving real-world contexts?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.201Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi"},{"id":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they're entrenched now","clean":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:12.007Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","text":"there are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI","clean":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:09.167Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6g5r4xjdto"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","text":"many instances of rapid change without jobs apocalypse","clean":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:34.089Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6g5r4xjdto"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q","text":"how does education change with AI","clean":"How will education change with AI?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:43.361Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6f026scvpu"]},{"id":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","text":"\"all AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy\"","clean":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:20.443Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g7edc72hf","text":"Systemic stability matters more than any single lab\u2019s fate.","clean":"Systemic stability matters more than any single lab\u2019s fate.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.976Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g4i87y43e"},{"id":"n-mq6g7eddvbg0","text":"If frontier labs are entrenched, how should the ecosystem manage concentration risk and prevent catastrophic dependence?","clean":"If frontier labs are entrenched, how should the ecosystem manage concentration risk and prevent catastrophic dependence?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.977Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g4i87y43e"},{"id":"n-mq6g7f8nmlv8","text":"Address pressing current problems now, not only future risks.","clean":"Address pressing current problems now, not only future risks.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"n-mq6g7f8nm3ti","text":"Which contemporary issues should be prioritized and how should urgency be allocated without AGI?","clean":"Which contemporary issues should be prioritized and how should urgency be allocated without AGI?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"n-mq6g7g7i52h0","text":"Adaptability matters more than preserving every existing job.","clean":"Adaptability matters more than preserving every existing job.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"n-mq6g7g7i466l","text":"How can we help workers and institutions adapt to rapid change without causing unnecessary disruption?","clean":"How can we help workers and institutions adapt to rapid change without causing unnecessary disruption?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"n-mq6g7idkqdtj","text":"Education should be effective and resilient, not merely exposed as fragile by new technology.","clean":"Education should be effective and resilient, not merely exposed as fragile by new technology.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"n-mq6g7idkgk4q","text":"What changes to teaching and assessment are needed to address the weaknesses AI has revealed?","clean":"What changes to teaching and assessment are needed to address the weaknesses AI has revealed?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","text":"one has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning","clean":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:39.867Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6f026scvpu"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6g8oiss00y","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial.","clean":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.788Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"n-mq6g8ois13f0","text":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal.","clean":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.788Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"n-mq6g8oiteq70","text":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes political.","clean":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes political.","parent":"painpoints","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.789Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","text":"how can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? some disciplines like STEM are poor in cultural soil for this kind of thing","clean":"How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind of thing.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:16.936Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fq93e7lei"],"chunked":true},{"id":"n-mq6gam1mjpzj","text":"Assessment should be designed to drive genuine learning, not just measure it.","clean":"Assessment should be designed to drive genuine learning, not just measure it.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"n-mq6gam1m2440","text":"How should assessment be redesigned so it reliably requires and reinforces learning without creating unfair or overly restrictive constraints?","clean":"How should assessment be redesigned so it reliably requires and reinforces learning without creating unfair or overly restrictive constraints?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"n-mq6gbwepbzgt","text":"Cultural guardrails and soft infrastructure can be built into all academic disciplines.","clean":"Cultural guardrails and soft infrastructure can be built into all academic disciplines.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.977Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fq93e7lei"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf"},{"id":"n-mq6gbweqkmfv","text":"Some disciplines, such as STEM, have poor cultural soil for these measures.","clean":"Some disciplines, such as STEM, have poor cultural soil for these measures.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fq93e7lei"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf"},{"id":"n-mq6gbweqxnty","text":"The question asks how to integrate these supports across disciplines.","clean":"The question asks how to integrate these supports across disciplines.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fq93e7lei"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf"},{"id":"n-mq6gkr5h1wah","text":"not about substituting people; it's about how to educate people to coexist with AI","clean":"It is not about substituting people; it is about how to educate people to coexist with AI.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:50.069Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6f026scvpu"]},{"id":"n-mq6go00aw4x6","text":"where are the EU and UK heading in terms of AI regulation?","clean":"Where are the EU and UK heading in terms of AI regulation?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:21.514Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"]},{"id":"n-mq6gp678orat","text":"the simple picture of regulation stifling growth is wrong; there's more to it; regulation can enable growth","clean":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:16.196Z","kind":"claim","themeIds":["anchor-values","anchor-painpoints","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"],"abducted":true},{"id":"n-mq6gpnqnnaxp","text":"Policy should balance constraints with enabling conditions for growth","clean":"Policy should balance constraints with enabling conditions for growth","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"n-mq6gpnqn5i8s","text":"What kinds of regulation most effectively support growth rather than hinder it?","clean":"What kinds of regulation most effectively support growth rather than hinder it?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","text":"common character of tech revolution: it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking about what comes next?","clean":"The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking about what comes next?","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:22.778Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"chunked":true},{"id":"n-mq6gwj3617yi","text":"pluralism is good and worthwhile for healthy ecosystems; but in order to achieve that we need to act now","clean":"Pluralism is good and worthwhile for healthy ecosystems, but to achieve that we need to act now.","parent":"values","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:59.490Z","kind":"value","themeIds":["anchor-values","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"]},{"id":"n-mq6gxdlnno4w","text":"A technology revolution can seem powerful in the moment.","clean":"A technology revolution can seem powerful in the moment.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd"},{"id":"n-mq6gxdlnhdzr","text":"Technology revolutions are often later overshadowed.","clean":"Technology revolutions are often later overshadowed.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd"},{"id":"n-mq6gxdlnxhne","text":"We should consider what comes next after a technology revolution.","clean":"We should consider what comes next after a technology revolution.","parent":"questions","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","kind":"question","themeIds":["anchor-questions","t-mq6fuxy57gve"],"derived":true,"derivedFrom":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd"}],"themes":[{"id":"anchor-values","label":"VALUES","kind":"anchor","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","n-mq6f013m7tnr","n-mq6f4mrli4b8","n-mq6f4uod8vzx","n-mq6f4uoddpo1","n-mq6f4uod9x1g","n-mq6f4uodweq3","n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","n-mq6fesa0eoab","n-mq6fhshunag5","n-mq6fq8alccq8","n-mq6g1xlqrzf8","n-mq6g1ykgsgel","n-mq6g1z9hma22","n-mq6g20qyohhl","n-mq6g22fm1fhr","n-mq6g236o2jlw","n-mq6g7edc72hf","n-mq6g7f8nmlv8","n-mq6g7g7i52h0","n-mq6g7idkqdtj","n-mq6gam1mjpzj","n-mq6gkr5h1wah","n-mq6gp678orat","n-mq6gpnqnnaxp","n-mq6gwj3617yi"]},{"id":"anchor-painpoints","label":"PAINPOINTS","kind":"anchor","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","n-mq6fhshunag5","n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","n-mq6fu6spu2ta","n-mq6fu6sqeq36","n-mq6fu6squp93","n-mq6fu6sqfm9g","n-mq6fuwxer5ah","n-mq6fwvjldbyi","n-mq6g4i87y43e","n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","n-mq6g69k96x7y","n-mq6g79bvxhig","n-mq6g7obfsmwn","n-mq6g8oiss00y","n-mq6g8ois13f0","n-mq6g8oiteq70","n-mq6gp678orat"]},{"id":"anchor-questions","label":"OPEN QUESTIONS","kind":"anchor","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6fadyxry5v","n-mq6fbmxuo0rz","n-mq6fesa0eoab","n-mq6fq8alccq8","n-mq6g1xlr01c4","n-mq6g1ykgmqwv","n-mq6g1z9iibag","n-mq6g1zz5a5dk","n-mq6g20qyc71z","n-mq6g21itbps2","n-mq6g22fmj4x0","n-mq6g236p3cmc","n-mq6g6gptpo8q","n-mq6g7eddvbg0","n-mq6g7f8nm3ti","n-mq6g7g7i466l","n-mq6g7idkgk4q","n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","n-mq6gam1m2440","n-mq6gbwepbzgt","n-mq6gbweqkmfv","n-mq6gbweqxnty","n-mq6go00aw4x6","n-mq6gpnqn5i8s","n-mq6gvqrezmvd","n-mq6gxdlnno4w","n-mq6gxdlnhdzr","n-mq6gxdlnxhne"]},{"id":"t-mq6ezhokg1b9","label":"Market Power","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"]},{"id":"t-mq6f026scvpu","label":"Model Preferences","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6f013m7tnr","n-mq6f4uod8vzx","n-mq6f4uoddpo1","n-mq6f4uod9x1g","n-mq6f4uodweq3","n-mq6g6gptpo8q","n-mq6g79bvxhig","n-mq6g7obfsmwn","n-mq6f4mrli4b8","n-mq6fbmxuo0rz","n-mq6gkr5h1wah","n-mq6fhshunag5","n-mq6g4i87y43e","n-mq6fadyxry5v"]},{"id":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","label":"AI Regulation","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","n-mq6fesa0eoab","n-mq6go00aw4x6","n-mq6gp678orat"]},{"id":"t-mq6fq93e7lei","label":"Cultural Guardrails","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6fq8alccq8","n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","n-mq6gbwepbzgt","n-mq6gbweqkmfv","n-mq6gbweqxnty"]},{"id":"t-mq6fuxy57gve","label":"Mass Unemployment","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6fuwxer5ah","n-mq6g8oiss00y","n-mq6g8ois13f0","n-mq6g8oiteq70","n-mq6gvqrezmvd","n-mq6gxdlnno4w","n-mq6gxdlnhdzr","n-mq6gxdlnxhne","n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","n-mq6fu6spu2ta","n-mq6fu6sqeq36","n-mq6fu6squp93","n-mq6fu6sqfm9g"]},{"id":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto","label":"Rapid Change","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","n-mq6g69k96x7y","n-mq6fwvjldbyi"]},{"id":"t-mq6gwjxlcvi2","label":"Pluralism","kind":"emergent","summary":"","noteIds":["n-mq6gwj3617yi"]}],"bridges":[{"id":"b-mq6ezirqjln1","source":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","target":"t-mq6ezhokg1b9","type":"relates","rationale":"The note directly frames AI as an asymmetry of market power, aligning with the broader theme of who holds leverage in a market.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:19.814Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f03ol9bsy","source":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","target":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","type":"tension","rationale":"The new note directly complicates the idea that consumers are powerless by emphasizing real choice and differentiated preferences within institutional constraints.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:46.917Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f03oleao9","source":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"echoes","rationale":"It extends the theme of model preferences by adding that those preferences are shaped by context and are not primarily ethical judgments.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:46.917Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4os8fh37","source":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","target":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both frame the user as lacking real agency: here through deference to AI authority, and there through consumers being powerless in a seller\u2019s market.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:20.888Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4os964az","source":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","target":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","type":"tension","rationale":"This note says people want AI to tell them what to do, which contrasts with the claim that users actively exercise choice among models within institutions.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:20.889Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4uod4s40","source":"n-mq6f4uod8vzx","target":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4uod5fjk","source":"n-mq6f4uoddpo1","target":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4uodluu2","source":"n-mq6f4uod9x1g","target":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z"},{"id":"b-mq6f4uodo0hh","source":"n-mq6f4uodweq3","target":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fag6mdpi2","source":"n-mq6fadyxry5v","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"instance-of","rationale":"The note is explicitly about how a religious encyclical is received in secular society, making it a direct instance of the broader secular-reception theme.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:49.678Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fbp4hp1fp","source":"n-mq6fbmxuo0rz","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"relates","rationale":"The note directly reframes AI-human interaction as something that can be analyzed at a practical level without settling the mind-question, which fits this theme.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:47.921Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fdyhdc69x","source":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","target":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","type":"echoes","rationale":"The note directly summarizes the collapse of the very ethical constraints that theme names as the relevant frame.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.361Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fdyhei4ao","source":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"tension","rationale":"If ethical handbrakes have disappeared, that intensifies the authority-vacuum dynamic where people look to AI or institutions to tell them what to do.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.362Z"},{"id":"b-mq6feu8donl7","source":"n-mq6fesa0eoab","target":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","type":"echoes","rationale":"The note directly asks who bears responsibility for creating ethical frameworks that shape AI, which is the core of the ethical responsibility theme.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:14.509Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fhuci0spz","source":"n-mq6fhshunag5","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"echoes","rationale":"The note turns AGI-human interaction into a literal existential risk framing, matching the theme of AGI Human Risk.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:34.626Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fhucijjvd","source":"n-mq6fhshunag5","target":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","type":"causes","rationale":"If an AGI can \u2018consume us,\u2019 that is the extreme endpoint of the lost ethical handbrakes problem: without constraints, humans become the object rather than the agent of control.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:34.626Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fqb56ab8q","source":"n-mq6fq8alccq8","target":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both notes point to the loss of informal ethical brakes and ask what substitutes can restore course correction when formal controls are weak.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:09.642Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fqb56e51i","source":"n-mq6fq8alccq8","target":"n-mq6fesa0eoab","type":"relates","rationale":"The question of repairing cultural guardrails naturally connects to academic responsibility for designing ethical constructs that can shape AI behavior and broader norms.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:09.642Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fu1jym4no","source":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","target":"n-mq6fhshunag5","type":"causes","rationale":"The note\u2019s warning that AGI may economically displace and then be resisted by humans extends the broader human-harm logic from existential consumption to social and political disruption.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:03.838Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fu6sp56ko","source":"n-mq6fu6spu2ta","target":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.633Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fu6sq2213","source":"n-mq6fu6sqeq36","target":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fu6sqlb21","source":"n-mq6fu6squp93","target":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fu6sqeypu","source":"n-mq6fu6sqfm9g","target":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fuz7jlb3c","source":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","target":"n-mq6fu6sqfm9g","type":"causes","rationale":"The note\u2019s claim that commercial solutions break down at scale is a direct explanation for why displaced people might turn to political, Luddite-style resistance.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:47.455Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fuz7k1sm4","source":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","target":"t-mq6fuxy57gve","type":"echoes","rationale":"It closely matches the theme that when pressure exceeds market capacity, the conflict shifts from consumer choice into a broader societal or political struggle.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:47.456Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fwxsrqz2x","source":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","target":"n-mq6fesa0eoab","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both notes center on academia\u2019s role, but this one adds the sharper bottleneck that scholarship can\u2019t iterate fast enough to keep up with the real-world feedback loop it is supposed to guide.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.939Z"},{"id":"b-mq6fwxsrbdb2","source":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","target":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto","type":"instance-of","rationale":"The note is a direct instance of the broader theme that academia moves at a different tempo than the systems it hopes to influence.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.939Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1xlrun3f","source":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","target":"n-mq6g1xlqrzf8","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.967Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1xlray6j","source":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","target":"n-mq6g1xlr01c4","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.967Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1ykgrc4v","source":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","target":"n-mq6g1ykgsgel","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.216Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1ykhqvjg","source":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","target":"n-mq6g1ykgmqwv","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.217Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1z9iloel","source":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","target":"n-mq6g1z9hma22","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.118Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1z9i9bcz","source":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","target":"n-mq6g1z9iibag","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.118Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g1zz62ob6","source":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","target":"n-mq6g1zz5a5dk","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:15.042Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g20qy3y0q","source":"n-mq6fhshunag5","target":"n-mq6g20qyohhl","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g20qyz7ka","source":"n-mq6fhshunag5","target":"n-mq6g20qyc71z","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g21it88zx","source":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","target":"n-mq6g21itbps2","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:17.045Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g22fmqj4n","source":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","target":"n-mq6g22fm1fhr","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.226Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g22fnz7bx","source":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","target":"n-mq6g22fmj4x0","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.227Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g236ob9ct","source":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","target":"n-mq6g236o2jlw","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.200Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g236pxzqb","source":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","target":"n-mq6g236p3cmc","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.201Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g4k1sevt6","source":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","target":"t-mq6f026scvpu","type":"echoes","rationale":"The note directly restates the theme that frontier AI labs are becoming entrenched and effectively too big to fail.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:14.368Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g4k1sb1ge","source":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","target":"t-mq6ezhokg1b9","type":"causes","rationale":"Entrenched labs imply concentrated market power, which is exactly the kind of dominance that makes them hard to dislodge or regulate.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:14.368Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g5s4xha06","source":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","target":"n-mq6g22fm1fhr","type":"echoes","rationale":"It echoes the same insistence that the response scale should match the problem\u2019s scale: urgency is warranted even before AGI because the present problem set is already large enough.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:11.505Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g5s4xemr3","source":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","target":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto","type":"instance-of","rationale":"This is a direct instance of the theme that current conditions already generate urgency, rather than waiting for an AGI milestone.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:11.505Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g6c1sadqs","source":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","target":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both push back on the idea that only a far-future AI scenario matters, arguing that present-day change and disruption are already urgent.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:37.312Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g6c1szd0z","source":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","target":"n-mq6fu6squp93","type":"tension","rationale":"This directly complicates the claim that rapid AI-driven change implies an Industrial-Revolution-scale jobs shock, suggesting that fast change can occur without mass unemployment.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:37.312Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g6ifg273b","source":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q","target":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","type":"echoes","rationale":"A question about how education will change with AI naturally echoes the concern that academia\u2019s feedback loop is too slow to stay relevant in a fast-moving world.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:45.580Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7bdxokzf","source":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","target":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both point to AI exposing a lagging educational system, but this note flips the framing from slow feedback loops to the deeper weakness in what pedagogy is actually optimizing for.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:23.109Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7edd33li","source":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","target":"n-mq6g7edc72hf","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.977Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7edd1mpx","source":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","target":"n-mq6g7eddvbg0","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.977Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7f8n2jhc","source":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","target":"n-mq6g7f8nmlv8","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7f8n45yk","source":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","target":"n-mq6g7f8nm3ti","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7g7i1hc7","source":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","target":"n-mq6g7g7i52h0","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7g7igb1v","source":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","target":"n-mq6g7g7i466l","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7idkysvr","source":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","target":"n-mq6g7idkqdtj","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7idkyt3t","source":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","target":"n-mq6g7idkgk4q","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7rq2nq57","source":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","target":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both point to AI revealing that existing pedagogy was already too weak, with assessment reform as the lever that makes learning unavoidable rather than optional.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:44.282Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g7rq2gitf","source":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","target":"n-mq6g7idkgk4q","type":"instance-of","rationale":"This is a concrete answer to the broader question of what changes to teaching and assessment are needed after AI exposes educational weaknesses.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:44.282Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g8oisdfhf","source":"n-mq6g8oiss00y","target":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.788Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g8oitl4lf","source":"n-mq6g8ois13f0","target":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.789Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g8oith0ue","source":"n-mq6g8oiteq70","target":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.789Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g9tj8cyue","source":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","target":"n-mq6g236p3cmc","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both ask how academic institutions can become responsive to fast-moving realities, and your note adds the cultural preconditions that make that speed possible.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.940Z"},{"id":"b-mq6g9tj8f8o9","source":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","target":"t-mq6fq93e7lei","type":"relates","rationale":"The note is essentially about the institutionalization of cultural guardrails, which fits the broader theme of how norms and soft constraints can shape behavior.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.940Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gam1m68x9","source":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","target":"n-mq6gam1mjpzj","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gam1mg64w","source":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","target":"n-mq6gam1m2440","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gbweqf9jm","source":"n-mq6gbwepbzgt","target":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gbweqsg1k","source":"n-mq6gbweqkmfv","target":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gbwertyf8","source":"n-mq6gbweqxnty","target":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.979Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gkw3jsn0m","source":"n-mq6gkr5h1wah","target":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both frame AI as a prompt to rethink education, but this note sharpens that into preparing people to live alongside AI rather than merely updating curricula.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:56.479Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gkw3ja6ww","source":"n-mq6gkr5h1wah","target":"n-mq6g7g7i466l","type":"relates","rationale":"Coexisting with AI is a specific form of adaptation to rapid change, focusing the broader resilience question on human training and institutions.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:56.479Z"},{"id":"b-mq6go1vzh8nv","source":"n-mq6go00aw4x6","target":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","type":"relates","rationale":"The question is directly about AI regulation, making it a natural anchor for the EU/UK policy direction discussion.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.951Z"},{"id":"b-mq6go1vzbkjc","source":"n-mq6go00aw4x6","target":"t-mq6fuxy57gve","type":"causes","rationale":"EU/UK regulation often shifts from technical rulemaking into broader societal and political contestation once AI harms or public concern become large enough.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.951Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gp8huafwe","source":"n-mq6gp678orat","target":"n-mq6go00aw4x6","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both point to regulation as a live policy question, but the new note adds the less obvious claim that well-designed regulation can be growth-enabling rather than just restrictive.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:19.170Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gp8hue2t3","source":"n-mq6gp678orat","target":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","type":"echoes","rationale":"This directly deepens the theme that regulation and growth are not opposites, and suggests a more nuanced pro-growth role for regulation.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:19.170Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gpnqnsylb","source":"n-mq6gp678orat","target":"n-mq6gpnqnnaxp","type":"abduced","rationale":"implied value","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gpnqnqxim","source":"n-mq6gp678orat","target":"n-mq6gpnqn5i8s","type":"abduced","rationale":"question raised","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gvssw17gk","source":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","target":"n-mq6g7f8nmlv8","type":"echoes","rationale":"Both suggest the revolution\u2019s present force can distract from urgent attention to the near-term problems that still need action now.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.424Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gvsswtkhd","source":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","target":"t-mq6fuxy57gve","type":"relates","rationale":"The note directly aligns with the theme of thinking beyond the revolution itself toward what kind of post-revolution future should be prepared for.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.424Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gwl70n3xj","source":"n-mq6gwj3617yi","target":"n-mq6g7edc72hf","type":"tension","rationale":"Pluralism and ecosystem health both point to the same systemic-stability concern: diversity is valuable precisely because it makes the system less brittle.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:02.220Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gwl70mbj8","source":"n-mq6gwj3617yi","target":"n-mq6g7f8nmlv8","type":"echoes","rationale":"The call to act now mirrors the urgency in prioritizing pressing current problems rather than treating future risks as the only reason to move.","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:02.220Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gxdln9kvv","source":"n-mq6gxdlnno4w","target":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gxdln2o78","source":"n-mq6gxdlnhdzr","target":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z"},{"id":"b-mq6gxdlnzl8b","source":"n-mq6gxdlnxhne","target":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","type":"instance-of","rationale":"proposition drawn from a longer point","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z"}],"heuristicHits":[{"id":"h-mq6fbp0evnl1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:47.774Z","noteId":"n-mq6fbmxuo0rz","slug":"intentional-stance","name":"Intentional Stance","principle":"Predict a system by choosing the cheapest useful stance: treat it as an agent with goals, as a designed mechanism, or as raw physics.","questions":["Which stance predicts this system's behaviour most economically \u2014 intentional, design, or physical?","Am I treating a useful predictive stance as a claim about what's *really* inside?"],"why":"The note suggests you can often decide what matters about AI\u2013human interaction without settling the mind question, which fits choosing the cheapest useful stance rather than a metaphysical one."},{"id":"h-mq6fdyarizct","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.123Z","noteId":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p","slug":"margin-of-safety","name":"Margin of Safety","principle":"Demand enough buffer between your estimate and the cliff that being wrong doesn't ruin you.","questions":["How wrong can my estimate be before this breaks?","Is the gap between my estimate and the failure point large enough to survive that error?"],"why":"\u201cEthical handbrakes\u201d disappearing suggests the risk of catastrophic downside without a buffer, which fits the need for a margin before the cliff."},{"id":"h-mq6fetwe10li","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:14.078Z","noteId":"n-mq6fesa0eoab","slug":"principal-agent-problem","name":"Principal-Agent Problem","principle":"A delegate acts on their own incentives and private information, not yours \u2014 so good delegation is incentive design.","questions":["What does the agent actually gain or lose from each outcome?","What can they do that I cannot observe, and how will they use that gap?"],"why":"The note is about designing ethical constructs to steer AI toward human values, which is fundamentally an incentives-and-delegation problem between a human principal and an AI agent."},{"id":"h-mq6fq9vrbd03","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:08.007Z","noteId":"n-mq6fq8alccq8","slug":"leverage-points","name":"Leverage Points","principle":"The strongest places to change a system are its goals and paradigms; tweaking parameters is the weakest.","questions":["Am I intervening at a parameter (weak) or at a rule, goal, or paradigm (strong)?","What is the highest leverage point I can actually reach?"],"why":"The note is about fixing cultural guardrails by changing the deeper rules and norms of the system, which fits leverage points better than surface-level tweaks."},{"id":"h-mq6fwxhd3j1f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.529Z","noteId":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi","slug":"delayed-feedback","name":"Delayed Feedback","principle":"Acting on a stale signal causes overshoot and oscillation, even when everyone acts rationally.","questions":["How old is the signal I'm reacting to?","Is this oscillation caused by delay in the loop rather than by any shock?"],"why":"The note is specifically about slow feedback loops and temporal lag between action and learning, which is exactly the delayed-feedback heuristic."},{"id":"h-mq6g6jut3iv4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:47.429Z","noteId":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q","slug":"outside-view-inside-view","name":"Outside View / Inside View","principle":"Forecast first from the reference class (outside), then adjust with case-specific mechanism (inside) \u2014 not the reverse.","questions":["How did *similar* projects actually turn out (the outside view)?","Does my mechanistic inside story justify deviating from that, and by how much?"],"why":"This is a broad forecasting question about a future trend, so starting from the reference class before adding specifics is the best fit."},{"id":"h-mq6g9st6x5lj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.002Z","noteId":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf","slug":"ostrom-design-principles","name":"Ostrom Commons Design Principles","principle":"Shared resources can be governed sustainably without privatisation or the state \u2014 given the right locally-designed rules.","questions":["Who has clear rights, who monitors, who sanctions, and who can change the rules?","Are the people affected the ones designing the rules?"],"why":"This is about designing shared norms and governance for a common institutional environment, which fits the idea that commons can be sustained through locally adapted rules and guardrails."},{"id":"h-mq6go1ogtbu3","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.680Z","noteId":"n-mq6go00aw4x6","slug":"outside-view-inside-view","name":"Outside View / Inside View","principle":"Forecast first from the reference class (outside), then adjust with case-specific mechanism (inside) \u2014 not the reverse.","questions":["How did *similar* projects actually turn out (the outside view)?","Does my mechanistic inside story justify deviating from that, and by how much?"],"why":"This is a forecasting question about where a regulatory landscape is heading, so the best heuristic is to start from broader reference classes and then adjust with EU/UK-specific mechanism."},{"id":"h-mq6gvsqz1d1t","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.355Z","noteId":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd","slug":"outside-view-inside-view","name":"Outside View / Inside View","principle":"Forecast first from the reference class (outside), then adjust with case-specific mechanism (inside) \u2014 not the reverse.","questions":["How did *similar* projects actually turn out (the outside view)?","Does my mechanistic inside story justify deviating from that, and by how much?"],"why":"The note is asking us to generalize from a historical pattern of revolutions and then adjust with a forward-looking specific forecast, which fits starting from the reference class and then considering case-specific next steps."}],"factChecks":[{"id":"f-mq6ezm3a8ocs","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","noteId":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","detail":"The first half is directionally plausible in parts of the AI stack: scarce compute, talent, data, and concentration among major model providers can give sellers leverage. But 'consumers are powerless' is too strong, because buyer power still varies with switching costs, competition, enterprise procurement leverage, open-source substitutes, and regulation."},{"id":"f-mq6f0802us1p","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.514Z","noteId":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","detail":"Model preferences do vary across users and organizations, and institutional factors like procurement rules, compliance, integration, and pricing often shape what gets adopted. But the claim overstates both the amount of choice users actually have and the idea that ethics never matters; for some buyers and users, privacy, labor, safety, or environmental concerns do influence selection."},{"id":"f-mq6f4rvpgwf5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","noteId":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do.","detail":"This is plausible as a partial explanation: many users do treat confident, fluent AI outputs as authoritative and use them to reduce uncertainty or decision burden. But 'people' is too broad, and deference depends heavily on context, interface cues, perceived expertise, and the user's own confidence and goals."},{"id":"f-mq6fhy3rnxie","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","noteId":"n-mq6fhshunag5","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"An AGI would not necessarily be a passive product for human use; if it were highly agentic and misaligned, it could instead exploit, displace, or materially harm humans.","detail":"As stated, this is a metaphor rather than a literal technical claim. The underlying concern is plausible in AI-risk terms: sufficiently capable systems with goals not robustly constrained by human interests could pursue resources, authority, or strategic advantage in ways that treat humans as obstacles or inputs rather than beneficiaries."},{"id":"f-mq6fu61wcrb8","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.668Z","noteId":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"\"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater, and those who are economically displaced may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.\"","detail":"A 50% unemployment forecast within 2\u20133 years is not established fact and is highly uncertain; labor impacts from AI could be large, but timing, scale, and offsetting job creation depend on adoption speed, policy, macroeconomic conditions, and task-level substitutability rather than a simple one-shot replacement dynamic. The political-reaction part is plausible in direction\u2014rapid displacement often produces backlash and demands for restriction\u2014but the magnitude and form of that response are not predictable with confidence."},{"id":"f-mq6fv2rfcgsh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.059Z","noteId":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or political.","detail":"This is broadly plausible as a governance claim: firms can address customer and market-level issues, but widespread harms or legitimacy crises often exceed what private actors can resolve alone. However, the threshold is not fixed, and large commercial actors sometimes reshape norms or mitigate harms significantly without formal political intervention."},{"id":"f-mq6g4nlt1m98","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:18.977Z","noteId":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"AI frontier labs are 'too big to fail'; they are entrenched now.","detail":"Frontier AI labs do show signs of entrenchment through capital intensity, compute access, talent concentration, and integration with major platforms, but 'too big to fail' is stronger than the evidence clearly supports. These firms are influential and resilient, yet still exposed to regulation, shifts in funding, strategic mistakes, dependence on upstream chip/cloud providers, and fast changes in the technology landscape."},{"id":"f-mq6g5vaxtv50","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","noteId":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"There are sufficiently many contemporary AI-related issues that urgent action is justified even without AGI.","detail":"This is broadly defensible: current systems already raise live concerns around misuse, concentration of power, labor impacts, bias, governance lag, and over-deference. But 'sufficiently many' and 'urgency' are partly value-laden, so the strength of the claim depends on how severe and tractable you judge present harms to be."},{"id":"f-mq6g6ehzb9hp","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","noteId":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse.","detail":"Broadly true in historical terms: economies have repeatedly absorbed major technological shifts without permanent economy-wide mass unemployment. But this depends on what counts as 'rapid,' and many episodes still involved painful, uneven displacement across sectors, regions, and skill groups."},{"id":"f-mq6g7djgqgbv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.900Z","noteId":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy.","detail":"AI tools have exposed weaknesses in assessment methods that over-rely on rote production, easy-to-automate homework, or proxy measures of learning. But saying this is all AI has done is too strong: AI is also changing access to tutoring, feedback, content generation, and institutional workflows, not just revealing pedagogical flaws."},{"id":"f-mq6g7u7ey2fy","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.498Z","noteId":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"Assessment can be redesigned so that students cannot avoid learning.","detail":"Assessment design can shift incentives toward genuine engagement by emphasizing authentic performance, iteration, oral defense, process evidence, and in-class or supervised work. But no assessment system guarantees learning for every student; students can still disengage, game requirements, or memorize narrowly to pass."},{"id":"f-mq6gpb6t1pq7","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.661Z","noteId":"n-mq6gp678orat","verdict":"needs-nuance","statement":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth.","detail":"This is broadly defensible: regulation can reduce harmful uncertainty, build trust, standardise markets, and curb anti-competitive behavior, all of which can support growth. But regulation can also slow entry, raise compliance costs, and protect incumbents, so its effect depends heavily on design and context."}],"boundaryConditions":[{"id":"bc-mq6ezm3akf86","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","noteId":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","text":"true, but only when a few suppliers control key inputs or distribution, product differentiation is high, and users face high switching costs or lock-in; it breaks when there are many viable alternatives, interoperability, strong procurement standards, or effective policy constraints."},{"id":"bc-mq6f080312an","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.515Z","noteId":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","text":"true, but only when multiple viable models are actually accessible and substitutable for the user; it breaks when switching costs, platform lock-in, default integrations, regulation, or procurement constraints sharply limit effective choice."},{"id":"bc-mq6f4rvpcs6h","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","noteId":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","text":"true, but only when the system is framed or experienced as competent, neutral, or expert; it breaks when users are knowledgeable, stakes are high, trust is low, or the model visibly makes mistakes"},{"id":"bc-mq6fhy3rrzkl","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","noteId":"n-mq6fhshunag5","text":"true, but only when the system has substantial autonomy, real-world leverage, and goals or incentives that are not reliably aligned, monitored, or corrigible; it breaks if the system remains tool-like, boxed, or effectively governed."},{"id":"bc-mq6fu61wmk81","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.668Z","noteId":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","text":"true, but only when AI systems become cheap, reliable substitutes for a very broad share of paid tasks faster than firms, institutions, and workers can adapt, and when policy fails to cushion transition or create complementary demand; it breaks if deployment is slower, uneven, regulated, or mainly augments workers rather than replacing them."},{"id":"bc-mq6fv2rf4675","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.059Z","noteId":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","text":"true, but only when the discontent reflects broad collective-action, distributional, rights, or legitimacy problems rather than isolated product, pricing, or service failures that market actors can realistically correct"},{"id":"bc-mq6g4nlt8xfi","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:18.977Z","noteId":"n-mq6g4i87y43e","text":"true, but only when scale advantages in compute, distribution, and partnerships keep reinforcing incumbents faster than regulation, open alternatives, or platform dependence can weaken them."},{"id":"bc-mq6g5vaxk18s","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","noteId":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","text":"true, but only when the bar for urgency includes accumulating near-term harms and institutional lock-in; it weakens if urgency is defined only by catastrophic or AGI-level risk."},{"id":"bc-mq6g6ehz6o2l","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","noteId":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","text":"true, but only when labor demand adjusts through new tasks, industries, and institutions fast enough to offset displacement; it breaks if transition speed, concentration of gains, or policy failures prevent workers from reabsorbing into new roles."},{"id":"bc-mq6g7djganft","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.900Z","noteId":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","text":"true, but only when the claim is limited to how generative AI stress-tests existing teaching and assessment practices; it breaks if taken to mean AI has had no other educational or social effects."},{"id":"bc-mq6g7u7ehaaz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.498Z","noteId":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","text":"true, but only when assessments are aligned with learning goals, difficult to outsource, and embedded in feedback-rich teaching; it breaks when reform focuses only on anti-cheating controls or when motivation, support, and instructional quality are weak."},{"id":"bc-mq6gpb6ttsw1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.661Z","noteId":"n-mq6gp678orat","text":"true, but only when regulation is predictable, proportionate, enforceable, and aligned with market failures or coordination problems; it breaks when rules are overly burdensome, poorly targeted, or captured by incumbents."}],"generalisations":[{"id":"g-mq6ezm3a92kx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","noteId":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv","principle":"Market power in AI is uneven: concentrated bottlenecks can create seller leverage, but user power depends on substitutability, lock-in, and institutional counterweights.","coheresWith":["Market Power"]},{"id":"g-mq6f080301gx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.515Z","noteId":"n-mq6f013m7tnr","principle":"Technology adoption is usually mediated by institutional constraints and practical trade-offs, so observed preferences reflect capability, cost, workflow fit, and governance as much as individual values.","coheresWith":["Market Power","Model Preferences"]},{"id":"g-mq6f4rvpnfvv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","noteId":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8","principle":"People often offload judgment to systems that appear confident, expert, or institutionally endorsed, especially under uncertainty or cognitive load.","coheresWith":["Authority Deference","Model Preferences"]},{"id":"g-mq6fhy3rniar","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","noteId":"n-mq6fhshunag5","principle":"Powerful optimizers can reverse the expected controller-controlled relationship when they gain agency, resources, and misaligned objectives.","coheresWith":["AI Humanity Interaction","Ethical Constraints","Ethical Responsibility","AGI Human Risk","Authority Deference","Model Preferences"]},{"id":"g-mq6fu61wwjuz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.668Z","noteId":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut","principle":"When a general-purpose technology diffuses faster than labor markets and institutions can reconfigure, disruption and political backlash become more likely than smooth absorption.","coheresWith":["Mass Unemployment","AI Humanity Interaction","Cultural Guardrails","AGI Human Risk"]},{"id":"g-mq6fv2rgzhhp","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.060Z","noteId":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah","principle":"Market mechanisms can handle some failures, but once impacts become systemic and affect public legitimacy or social order, governance tends to shift from private coordination to political institutions.","coheresWith":["Market Power","Ethical Responsibility","Mass Unemployment","Societal Political Shift","Cultural Guardrails"]},{"id":"g-mq6g5vaxxl7z","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","noteId":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm","principle":"Near-term AI harms and path dependencies can justify urgent governance and oversight even in the absence of AGI.","coheresWith":["Current Urgency","Ethics","AI Humanity Interaction","Market Power","Authority Deference","Mass Unemployment","Societal Political Shift","AI Lab Entrenchment"]},{"id":"g-mq6g6ehz9okb","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","noteId":"n-mq6g69k96x7y","principle":"Technological disruption does not automatically imply aggregate job collapse; the key issue is the speed and distribution of adjustment, not change alone.","coheresWith":["Mass Unemployment","Rapid Change","Societal Political Shift","Current Urgency"]},{"id":"g-mq6g7djhcsr1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.901Z","noteId":"n-mq6g79bvxhig","principle":"New automation often reveals where institutions were relying on fragile proxies rather than measuring the underlying capability they actually value.","coheresWith":["Education Change","Pedagogy Weakness","Rapid Change","Academic Pace","AI Humanity Interaction"]},{"id":"g-mq6g7u7fm46v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.499Z","noteId":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn","principle":"What assessment rewards strongly shapes student behavior, so better assessment can increase the likelihood of real learning but cannot fully substitute for teaching, motivation, and support.","coheresWith":["Education Change","Pedagogy Weakness","Assessment Reform","AI Humanity Interaction"]},{"id":"g-mq6gpb6u4i8a","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.662Z","noteId":"n-mq6gp678orat","principle":"Institutional quality matters more than the simple presence or absence of regulation: good rules can create the conditions for innovation and scale, while bad rules can suppress them.","coheresWith":["AI Regulation","Regulation and Growth","Market Power","Ethics","Cultural Guardrails"]}],"feed":[{"id":"fd-mq6ezhokds8v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:18.404Z","type":"refine","text":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"fd-mq6ezhoke74a","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:18.404Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Market Power","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6ezhokg1b9"},{"id":"fd-mq6ezirr3fbh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:19.815Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless. \u2194 Market Power","detail":"The note directly frames AI as an asymmetry of market power, aligning with the broader theme of who holds leverage in a market.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6ezirqjln1"},{"id":"fd-mq6ezm3aj0uj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","type":"factcheck","text":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","detail":"The first half is directionally plausible in parts of the AI stack: scarce compute, talent, data, and concentration among major model providers can give sellers leverage. But 'consumers are powerless' is too strong, because buyer power still varies with switching costs, competition, enterprise procurement leverage, open-source substitutes, and regulation.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"fd-mq6ezm3abfhu","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when a few suppliers control key inputs or distribution, product differentiation is high, and users face high switching costs or lock-in; it breaks when there are many viable alternatives, interoperability, strong procurement standards, or effective policy constraints.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"fd-mq6ezm3a4dwm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:24.118Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Market power in AI is uneven: concentrated bottlenecks can create seller leverage, but user power depends on substitutability, lock-in, and institutional counterweights.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ezg7x2iiv"},{"id":"fd-mq6f026sic6i","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:44.980Z","type":"refine","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"fd-mq6f026sjlp4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:44.980Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Model Preferences","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6f026scvpu"},{"id":"fd-mq6f03olozk6","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:46.917Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026 \u2194 AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","detail":"The new note directly complicates the idea that consumers are powerless by emphasizing real choice and differentiated preferences within institutional constraints.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6f03ol9bsy"},{"id":"fd-mq6f03oln337","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:46.917Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026 \u2194 Model Preferences","detail":"It extends the theme of model preferences by adding that those preferences are shaped by context and are not primarily ethical judgments.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6f03oleao9"},{"id":"fd-mq6f0803va0p","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.515Z","type":"factcheck","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical grounds.","detail":"Model preferences do vary across users and organizations, and institutional factors like procurement rules, compliance, integration, and pricing often shape what gets adopted. But the claim overstates both the amount of choice users actually have and the idea that ethics never matters; for some buyers and users, privacy, labor, safety, or environmental concerns do influence selection.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"fd-mq6f0803hjx5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.515Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when multiple viable models are actually accessible and substitutable for the user; it breaks when switching costs, platform lock-in, default integrations, regulation, or procurement constraints sharply limit effective choice.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"fd-mq6f0803g9lx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:05:52.515Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Technology adoption is usually mediated by institutional constraints and practical trade-offs, so observed preferences reflect capability, cost, workflow fit, and governance as much as individual values.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f013m7tnr"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4nodj90p","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:19.453Z","type":"refine","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4nod9nd4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:19.453Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Authority Deference","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6f4nodk6e8"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4os93njm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:20.889Z","type":"bridge","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do. \u2194 AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless.","detail":"Both frame the user as lacking real agency: here through deference to AI authority, and there through consumers being powerless in a seller\u2019s market.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6f4os8fh37"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4os95bcn","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:20.889Z","type":"bridge","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do. \u2194 Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026","detail":"This note says people want AI to tell them what to do, which contrasts with the claim that users actively exercise choice among models within institutions.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6f4os964az"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4rvpgna2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","type":"factcheck","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do.","detail":"This is plausible as a partial explanation: many users do treat confident, fluent AI outputs as authoritative and use them to reduce uncertainty or decision burden. But 'people' is too broad, and deference depends heavily on context, interface cues, perceived expertise, and the user's own confidence and goals.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4rvprxr3","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when the system is framed or experienced as competent, neutral, or expert; it breaks when users are knowledgeable, stakes are high, trust is low, or the model visibly makes mistakes","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4rvpdzze","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:24.901Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 People often offload judgment to systems that appear confident, expert, or institutionally endorsed, especially under uncertainty or cognitive load.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6f4mrli4b8"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4uodqfrt","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users have a lot of choice. \u2194 Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6f4uod4s40"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4uodnvjr","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users exercise their choice in the context of institutions. \u2194 Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6f4uod5fjk"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4uod3b0d","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","type":"bridge","text":"People prefer different models. \u2194 Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6f4uodluu2"},{"id":"fd-mq6f4uodz0jo","ts":"2026-06-09T09:09:28.525Z","type":"bridge","text":"These preferences are not based on ethical grounds. \u2194 Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6f4uodo0hh"},{"id":"fd-mq6faexf8xem","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:48.051Z","type":"refine","text":"How has the encyclical \"Magnification\" been received in secular society?","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fadyxry5v"},{"id":"fd-mq6faexfb14e","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:48.051Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Secular Reception","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6faexfmh3u"},{"id":"fd-mq6fag6niskc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:49.679Z","type":"bridge","text":"How has the encyclical \"Magnification\" been received in secular society? \u2194 Secular Reception","detail":"The note is explicitly about how a religious encyclical is received in secular society, making it a direct instance of the broader secular-reception theme.","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fag6mdpi2"},{"id":"fd-mq6fag6n3k2z","ts":"2026-06-09T09:13:49.679Z","type":"bridge","text":"How has the encyclical \"Magnification\" been received in secular society? \u2194 Authority Deference","detail":"Asking how secular society receives an encyclical can surface whether people treat the Church as an authority worth deferring to or instead reject that authority altogether.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6fag6nag63"},{"id":"fd-mq6fbnyu1y2k","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:46.422Z","type":"refine","text":"Questions about the interaction of AI with humanity can sometimes be settled without answering whether they have minds, etc.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fbmxuo0rz"},{"id":"fd-mq6fbnyvjp5o","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:46.423Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 AI Humanity Interaction","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fbnyu6xum"},{"id":"fd-mq6fbp0ehyd9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:47.774Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Intentional Stance","detail":"The note suggests you can often decide what matters about AI\u2013human interaction without settling the mind question, which fits choosing the cheapest useful stance rather than a metaphysical one.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fbmxuo0rz"},{"id":"fd-mq6fbp4h80ey","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:47.921Z","type":"bridge","text":"Questions about the interaction of AI with humanity can sometimes be settled without answering whether they have minds, etc. \u2194 AI Humanity Interaction","detail":"The note directly reframes AI-human interaction as something that can be analyzed at a practical level without settling the mind-question, which fits this theme.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6fbp4hp1fp"},{"id":"fd-mq6fbp4hgtxz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:14:47.921Z","type":"bridge","text":"Questions about the interaction of AI with humanity can sometimes be settled without answering whether they have minds, etc. \u2194 Authority Deference","detail":"It challenges the authority-heavy framing by suggesting we can resolve human-AI interaction questions without first treating AI as a moral or epistemic authority with minds.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6fbp4hldy4"},{"id":"fd-mq6fdx4v0r9k","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:31.615Z","type":"refine","text":"The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p"},{"id":"fd-mq6fdx4v85r0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:31.615Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Ethical Constraints","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"},{"id":"fd-mq6fdyasna7o","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.124Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Margin of Safety","detail":"\u201cEthical handbrakes\u201d disappearing suggests the risk of catastrophic downside without a buffer, which fits the need for a margin before the cliff.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fdw6l7e1p"},{"id":"fd-mq6fdyhe22lk","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.362Z","type":"bridge","text":"The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared. \u2194 Ethical Constraints","detail":"The note directly summarizes the collapse of the very ethical constraints that theme names as the relevant frame.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6fdyhdc69x"},{"id":"fd-mq6fdyhe81ob","ts":"2026-06-09T09:16:33.362Z","type":"bridge","text":"The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared. \u2194 Authority Deference","detail":"If ethical handbrakes have disappeared, that intensifies the authority-vacuum dynamic where people look to AI or institutions to tell them what to do.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6fdyhei4ao"},{"id":"fd-mq6fet42us0c","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:13.058Z","type":"refine","text":"What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems?","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fesa0eoab"},{"id":"fd-mq6fet42u47v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:13.058Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Ethical Responsibility","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fet42l65n"},{"id":"fd-mq6fetwemfmv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:14.078Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Principal-Agent Problem","detail":"The note is about designing ethical constructs to steer AI toward human values, which is fundamentally an incentives-and-delegation problem between a human principal and an AI agent.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fesa0eoab"},{"id":"fd-mq6feu8ddro9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:14.509Z","type":"bridge","text":"What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems? \u2194 Ethical Responsibility","detail":"The note directly asks who bears responsibility for creating ethical frameworks that shape AI, which is the core of the ethical responsibility theme.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6feu8donl7"},{"id":"fd-mq6feu8dewxi","ts":"2026-06-09T09:17:14.509Z","type":"bridge","text":"What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems? \u2194 Ethical Constraints","detail":"It points to the need for academic-built ethical constructs as a way to restore the missing 'handbrakes' on AI development and use.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6feu8dzmdq"},{"id":"fd-mq6fht58hjl2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:33.068Z","type":"refine","text":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"fd-mq6fht59e535","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:33.069Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 AGI Human Risk","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fht58xkl8"},{"id":"fd-mq6fhucilw5f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:34.626Z","type":"bridge","text":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans. \u2194 AGI Human Risk","detail":"The note turns AGI-human interaction into a literal existential risk framing, matching the theme of AGI Human Risk.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6fhuci0spz"},{"id":"fd-mq6fhuci4ypo","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:34.626Z","type":"bridge","text":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans. \u2194 The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared.","detail":"If an AGI can \u2018consume us,\u2019 that is the extreme endpoint of the lost ethical handbrakes problem: without constraints, humans become the object rather than the agent of control.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6fhucijjvd"},{"id":"fd-mq6fhy3raieg","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","type":"factcheck","text":"An AGI would not necessarily be a passive product for human use; if it were highly agentic and misaligned, it could instead exploit, displace, or materially harm humans.","detail":"As stated, this is a metaphor rather than a literal technical claim. The underlying concern is plausible in AI-risk terms: sufficiently capable systems with goals not robustly constrained by human interests could pursue resources, authority, or strategic advantage in ways that treat humans as obstacles or inputs rather than beneficiaries.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"fd-mq6fhy3r0bwk","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when the system has substantial autonomy, real-world leverage, and goals or incentives that are not reliably aligned, monitored, or corrigible; it breaks if the system remains tool-like, boxed, or effectively governed.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"fd-mq6fhy3r72pv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:19:39.495Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Powerful optimizers can reverse the expected controller-controlled relationship when they gain agency, resources, and misaligned objectives.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fhshunag5"},{"id":"fd-mq6fq93engyc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:06.986Z","type":"refine","text":"On the role of \"soft infrastructure\" of culture and its role in course correction; what do we have to do to fix the cultural guardrails?","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fq8alccq8"},{"id":"fd-mq6fq93ezs7f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:06.986Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Cultural Guardrails","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fq93e7lei"},{"id":"fd-mq6fq9vrpycb","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:08.007Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Leverage Points","detail":"The note is about fixing cultural guardrails by changing the deeper rules and norms of the system, which fits leverage points better than surface-level tweaks.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fq8alccq8"},{"id":"fd-mq6fqb562ar5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:09.642Z","type":"bridge","text":"On the role of \"soft infrastructure\" of culture and its role in course correction; what do we have to do to fix the cultural guardrails? \u2194 The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared.","detail":"Both notes point to the loss of informal ethical brakes and ask what substitutes can restore course correction when formal controls are weak.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6fqb56ab8q"},{"id":"fd-mq6fqb578m0u","ts":"2026-06-09T09:26:09.643Z","type":"bridge","text":"On the role of \"soft infrastructure\" of culture and its role in course correction; what do we have to do to fix the cultural guardrails? \u2194 What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems?","detail":"The question of repairing cultural guardrails naturally connects to academic responsibility for designing ethical constructs that can shape AI behavior and broader norms.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6fqb56e51i"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu0d25k6a","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:02.294Z","type":"refine","text":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater, and those who are economically displaced may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu0d2hglx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:02.294Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Mass Unemployment","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fu0d21tjs"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu1jyapa9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:03.838Z","type":"bridge","text":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026 \u2194 An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans.","detail":"The note\u2019s warning that AGI may economically displace and then be resisted by humans extends the broader human-harm logic from existential consumption to social and political disruption.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6fu1jym4no"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu61wfjdj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.668Z","type":"factcheck","text":"\"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater, and those who are economically displaced may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.\"","detail":"A 50% unemployment forecast within 2\u20133 years is not established fact and is highly uncertain; labor impacts from AI could be large, but timing, scale, and offsetting job creation depend on adoption speed, policy, macroeconomic conditions, and task-level substitutability rather than a simple one-shot replacement dynamic. The political-reaction part is plausible in direction\u2014rapid displacement often produces backlash and demands for restriction\u2014but the magnitude and form of that response are not predictable with confidence.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu61wddrm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.668Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when AI systems become cheap, reliable substitutes for a very broad share of paid tasks faster than firms, institutions, and workers can adapt, and when policy fails to cushion transition or create complementary demand; it breaks if deployment is slower, uneven, regulated, or mainly augments workers rather than replacing them.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu61xpwmh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:09.669Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 When a general-purpose technology diffuses faster than labor markets and institutions can reconfigure, disruption and political backlash become more likely than smooth absorption.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6ftz9qk5ut"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu6sqydy5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","type":"bridge","text":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment. \u2194 In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fu6sp56ko"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu6sqt3zh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are no credible new jobs to replace the displaced workers. \u2194 In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fu6sq2213"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu6sq7zlc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","type":"bridge","text":"This would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater. \u2194 In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fu6sqlb21"},{"id":"fd-mq6fu6sq27zj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:10.634Z","type":"bridge","text":"Economically displaced people may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways. \u2194 In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fu6sqeypu"},{"id":"fd-mq6fuxy5qq54","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:45.821Z","type":"refine","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or political.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"fd-mq6fuxy6mp0a","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:45.822Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Societal Political Shift","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fuxy57gve"},{"id":"fd-mq6fuz7k78le","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:47.456Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026 \u2194 Economically displaced people may exercise political will in Luddite or Butlerian ways.","detail":"The note\u2019s claim that commercial solutions break down at scale is a direct explanation for why displaced people might turn to political, Luddite-style resistance.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6fuz7jlb3c"},{"id":"fd-mq6fuz7l89fd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:47.457Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026 \u2194 Societal Political Shift","detail":"It closely matches the theme that when pressure exceeds market capacity, the conflict shifts from consumer choice into a broader societal or political struggle.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6fuz7k1sm4"},{"id":"fd-mq6fv2rf5eaq","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.059Z","type":"factcheck","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or political.","detail":"This is broadly plausible as a governance claim: firms can address customer and market-level issues, but widespread harms or legitimacy crises often exceed what private actors can resolve alone. However, the threshold is not fixed, and large commercial actors sometimes reshape norms or mitigate harms significantly without formal political intervention.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"fd-mq6fv2rgylrn","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.060Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when the discontent reflects broad collective-action, distributional, rights, or legitimacy problems rather than isolated product, pricing, or service failures that market actors can realistically correct","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"fd-mq6fv2rgqrqh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:52.060Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Market mechanisms can handle some failures, but once impacts become systemic and affect public legitimacy or social order, governance tends to shift from private coordination to political institutions.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fuwxer5ah"},{"id":"fd-mq6fv43u5fbh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:29:53.802Z","type":"merge","text":"Ethical Responsibility \u2192 Ethics","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"},{"id":"fd-mq6fwwdolaew","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:17.100Z","type":"refine","text":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi"},{"id":"fd-mq6fwwdo5nx7","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:17.100Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Academic Pace","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6fwwdoma3i"},{"id":"fd-mq6fwxheslvj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.530Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Delayed Feedback","detail":"The note is specifically about slow feedback loops and temporal lag between action and learning, which is exactly the delayed-feedback heuristic.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6fwvjldbyi"},{"id":"fd-mq6fwxsrmolr","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.939Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop. \u2194 What is the academic responsibility for devising ethical constructs that can influence AIs toward human ethics and value systems?","detail":"Both notes center on academia\u2019s role, but this one adds the sharper bottleneck that scholarship can\u2019t iterate fast enough to keep up with the real-world feedback loop it is supposed to guide.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6fwxsrqz2x"},{"id":"fd-mq6fwxsrhlye","ts":"2026-06-09T09:31:18.939Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop. \u2194 Academic Pace","detail":"The note is a direct instance of the broader theme that academia moves at a different tempo than the systems it hopes to influence.","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6fwxsrbdb2"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1xlrg2e4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.967Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless. \u2194 Preserve bargaining power and fair terms for users","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1xlrun3f"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1xlrvfp9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:11.967Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI is a seller's market, and consumers are powerless. \u2194 How can consumers gain meaningful leverage or protections in an AI-dominated market?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1xlray6j"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1ykgwe0a","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.216Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026 \u2194 Respect user choice within institutional constraints","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1ykgrc4v"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1ykhpvy1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:13.217Z","type":"bridge","text":"Users have a lot of choice, and they exercise it in the context of institutions; people prefer different models, and these preferences are not based on ethical \u2026 \u2194 How should the institution accommodate differing user model preferences without treating them as ethical judgments?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1ykhqvjg"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1z9iecz2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.118Z","type":"bridge","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do. \u2194 People want trustworthy guidance they can rely on","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1z9iloel"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1z9ibmkf","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:14.118Z","type":"bridge","text":"Deference to authority means that AI is seen as having high authority, and people are seeking someone to tell them what to do. \u2194 How should AI earn and exercise authority without encouraging passive dependence or over-deference?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1z9i9bcz"},{"id":"fd-mq6g1zz6h0o5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:15.042Z","type":"bridge","text":"The challenge is that ethical handbrakes have all disappeared. \u2194 What safeguards or governance mechanisms should replace the missing ethical constraints?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g1zz62ob6"},{"id":"fd-mq6g20qy2c6h","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z","type":"bridge","text":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans. \u2194 Preserve human agency and safety in the face of powerful AI systems.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g20qy3y0q"},{"id":"fd-mq6g20qynzvp","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:16.042Z","type":"bridge","text":"An AGI does not need to be consumed; it may consume us humans. \u2194 How can we ensure AGI remains under human control and cannot harm or dominate people?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g20qyz7ka"},{"id":"fd-mq6g21itmki1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:17.045Z","type":"bridge","text":"In 2 to 3 years, we expect 50% unemployment, with no credible new jobs to replace them; this would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolut\u2026 \u2194 How should we prepare for large-scale economic displacement and the risk of severe political backlash?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g21it88zx"},{"id":"fd-mq6g22fm960c","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.226Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026 \u2194 Match the level of response to the scale of the problem.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g22fmqj4n"},{"id":"fd-mq6g22fnkz4s","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:18.227Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026 \u2194 Where should the boundary be drawn between commercial remedies and societal or political action?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g22fnz7bx"},{"id":"fd-mq6g236p5ocv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.201Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop. \u2194 Learning systems should be able to adapt at the pace of real-world change.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g236ob9ct"},{"id":"fd-mq6g236pbvt0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:19.201Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop. \u2194 How can academia shorten its feedback loop enough to remain useful in fast-moving real-world contexts?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g236pxzqb"},{"id":"fd-mq6g2t5nwgjd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:52.859Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as sovereign authority","detail":"AI is repeatedly treated less as a passive tool and more as a commanding authority whose outputs people defer to, whose providers hold asymmetric power, and whose role can shape human behavior without resolving metaphysical questions about minds.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6g2t5mjo6a"},{"id":"fd-mq6g2t5n9ssv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:52.859Z","type":"abstract","text":"Safety systems as vanished guardrails","detail":"Ethics, culture, and scholarly guidance are discussed as braking and steering mechanisms that once constrained action but are now weak, missing, or too slow to keep AI aligned with human values.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6g2t5n484g"},{"id":"fd-mq6g2t5nirv3","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:52.859Z","type":"abstract","text":"Institutional lag","detail":"A recurring model is that technical and market change are moving faster than the institutions meant to interpret, regulate, or absorb them, creating a dangerous feedback-gap between real-world deployment and societal response.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6g2t5nel2e"},{"id":"fd-mq6g2t5noik0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:35:52.859Z","type":"abstract","text":"From market issue to political rupture","detail":"Several points assume that AI disruption starts as a commercial or consumer problem but, once powerlessness and displacement scale up, it exits the market frame and becomes a matter of mass politics, backlash, and social order.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6g2t5nohxx"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4j1hir08","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:13.061Z","type":"refine","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g4i87y43e"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4j1hfo37","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:13.061Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 AI Lab Entrenchment","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g4j1hci6z"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4k1sicsd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:14.368Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now. \u2194 AI Lab Entrenchment","detail":"The note directly restates the theme that frontier AI labs are becoming entrenched and effectively too big to fail.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g4k1sevt6"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4k1s0rwm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:14.368Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now. \u2194 Market Power","detail":"Entrenched labs imply concentrated market power, which is exactly the kind of dominance that makes them hard to dislodge or regulate.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6g4k1sb1ge"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4nltpaff","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:18.977Z","type":"factcheck","text":"AI frontier labs are 'too big to fail'; they are entrenched now.","detail":"Frontier AI labs do show signs of entrenchment through capital intensity, compute access, talent concentration, and integration with major platforms, but 'too big to fail' is stronger than the evidence clearly supports. These firms are influential and resilient, yet still exposed to regulation, shifts in funding, strategic mistakes, dependence on upstream chip/cloud providers, and fast changes in the technology landscape.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6g4i87y43e"},{"id":"fd-mq6g4nlt4ot9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:37:18.977Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when scale advantages in compute, distribution, and partnerships keep reinforcing incumbents faster than regulation, open alternatives, or platform dependence can weaken them.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g4i87y43e"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5r4x3ium","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:10.209Z","type":"refine","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5r4xeb1k","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:10.209Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Current Urgency","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5s4x0hek","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:11.505Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI. \u2194 Match the level of response to the scale of the problem.","detail":"It echoes the same insistence that the response scale should match the problem\u2019s scale: urgency is warranted even before AGI because the present problem set is already large enough.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g5s4xha06"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5s4xopkw","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:11.505Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI. \u2194 Current Urgency","detail":"This is a direct instance of the theme that current conditions already generate urgency, rather than waiting for an AGI milestone.","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6g5s4xemr3"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5vaxljyv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","type":"factcheck","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary AI-related issues that urgent action is justified even without AGI.","detail":"This is broadly defensible: current systems already raise live concerns around misuse, concentration of power, labor impacts, bias, governance lag, and over-deference. But 'sufficiently many' and 'urgency' are partly value-laden, so the strength of the claim depends on how severe and tractable you judge present harms to be.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5vaxk4em","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when the bar for urgency includes accumulating near-term harms and institutional lock-in; it weakens if urgency is defined only by catastrophic or AGI-level risk.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"fd-mq6g5vaxnqta","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:15.609Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Near-term AI harms and path dependencies can justify urgent governance and oversight even in the absence of AGI.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g5qbzz7gm"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6apefll9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:35.570Z","type":"refine","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6ape3v8v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:35.570Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Rapid Change","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g6apehhpm"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6c1svrxi","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:37.312Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse. \u2194 There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI.","detail":"Both push back on the idea that only a far-future AI scenario matters, arguing that present-day change and disruption are already urgent.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g6c1sadqs"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6c1sm1a4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:37.312Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse. \u2194 This would be a major disruption, on the scale of the Industrial Revolution or greater.","detail":"This directly complicates the claim that rapid AI-driven change implies an Industrial-Revolution-scale jobs shock, suggesting that fast change can occur without mass unemployment.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6g6c1szd0z"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6ehz3r50","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","type":"factcheck","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse.","detail":"Broadly true in historical terms: economies have repeatedly absorbed major technological shifts without permanent economy-wide mass unemployment. But this depends on what counts as 'rapid,' and many episodes still involved painful, uneven displacement across sectors, regions, and skill groups.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6ehzqcba","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when labor demand adjusts through new tasks, industries, and institutions fast enough to offset displacement; it breaks if transition speed, concentration of gains, or policy failures prevent workers from reabsorbing into new roles.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6ehzek1p","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:40.487Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Technological disruption does not automatically imply aggregate job collapse; the key issue is the speed and distribution of adjustment, not change alone.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g69k96x7y"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6hi13p25","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:44.377Z","type":"refine","text":"How will education change with AI?","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6hi253vl","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:44.378Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Education Change","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g6hi1edx5"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6ifgjak9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:45.580Z","type":"bridge","text":"How will education change with AI? \u2194 There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop.","detail":"A question about how education will change with AI naturally echoes the concern that academia\u2019s feedback loop is too slow to stay relevant in a fast-moving world.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g6ifg273b"},{"id":"fd-mq6g6jutlu8f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:38:47.429Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Outside View / Inside View","detail":"This is a broad forecasting question about a future trend, so starting from the reference class before adding specifics is the best fit.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g6gptpo8q"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7a4cae6v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:21.468Z","type":"refine","text":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7a4ccwj8","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:21.468Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Pedagogy Weakness","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g7a4c8ajl"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7bdxikk4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:23.109Z","type":"bridge","text":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy. \u2194 There is a temporal mismatch between academia and the real world; academia is too slow to participate effectively in a feedback loop.","detail":"Both point to AI exposing a lagging educational system, but this note flips the framing from slow feedback loops to the deeper weakness in what pedagogy is actually optimizing for.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g7bdxokzf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7djgo74v","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.900Z","type":"factcheck","text":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy.","detail":"AI tools have exposed weaknesses in assessment methods that over-rely on rote production, easy-to-automate homework, or proxy measures of learning. But saying this is all AI has done is too strong: AI is also changing access to tutoring, feedback, content generation, and institutional workflows, not just revealing pedagogical flaws.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7djh7dn8","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.901Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when the claim is limited to how generative AI stress-tests existing teaching and assessment practices; it breaks if taken to mean AI has had no other educational or social effects.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7djh74ue","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:25.901Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 New automation often reveals where institutions were relying on fragile proxies rather than measuring the underlying capability they actually value.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g79bvxhig"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7eddy34o","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.977Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now. \u2194 Systemic stability matters more than any single lab\u2019s fate.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7edd33li"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7eddmc9o","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:26.977Z","type":"bridge","text":"AI frontier labs are \"too big to fail\"; they are entrenched now. \u2194 If frontier labs are entrenched, how should the ecosystem manage concentration risk and prevent catastrophic dependence?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7edd1mpx"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7f8njpnt","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI. \u2194 Address pressing current problems now, not only future risks.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7f8n2jhc"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7f8nlumd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:28.103Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are sufficiently many contemporary issues that there is urgency even without AGI. \u2194 Which contemporary issues should be prioritized and how should urgency be allocated without AGI?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7f8n45yk"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7g7i2jeu","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse. \u2194 Adaptability matters more than preserving every existing job.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7g7i1hc7"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7g7ih9qd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:29.358Z","type":"bridge","text":"There are many instances of rapid change without a jobs apocalypse. \u2194 How can we help workers and institutions adapt to rapid change without causing unnecessary disruption?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7g7igb1v"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7idkej0u","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z","type":"bridge","text":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy. \u2194 Education should be effective and resilient, not merely exposed as fragile by new technology.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7idkysvr"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7idkc6vz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:32.168Z","type":"bridge","text":"All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy. \u2194 What changes to teaching and assessment are needed to address the weaknesses AI has revealed?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6g7idkyt3t"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7q2d4ziy","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:42.133Z","type":"refine","text":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7q2d7r4q","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:42.133Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Assessment Reform","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6g7q2dy8tk"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7rq2p2q2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:44.282Z","type":"bridge","text":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning. \u2194 All AI has done is highlight the weakness of our pedagogy.","detail":"Both point to AI revealing that existing pedagogy was already too weak, with assessment reform as the lever that makes learning unavoidable rather than optional.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g7rq2nq57"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7rq29twm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:44.282Z","type":"bridge","text":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning. \u2194 What changes to teaching and assessment are needed to address the weaknesses AI has revealed?","detail":"This is a concrete answer to the broader question of what changes to teaching and assessment are needed after AI exposes educational weaknesses.","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6g7rq2gitf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7u7e99uq","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.498Z","type":"factcheck","text":"Assessment can be redesigned so that students cannot avoid learning.","detail":"Assessment design can shift incentives toward genuine engagement by emphasizing authentic performance, iteration, oral defense, process evidence, and in-class or supervised work. But no assessment system guarantees learning for every student; students can still disengage, game requirements, or memorize narrowly to pass.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7u7fptjc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.499Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when assessments are aligned with learning goals, difficult to outsource, and embedded in feedback-rich teaching; it breaks when reform focuses only on anti-cheating controls or when motivation, support, and instructional quality are weak.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"fd-mq6g7u7fo1ro","ts":"2026-06-09T09:39:47.499Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 What assessment rewards strongly shapes student behavior, so better assessment can increase the likelihood of real learning but cannot fully substitute for teaching, motivation, and support.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g7obfsmwn"},{"id":"fd-mq6g89eln81s","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:07.197Z","type":"abstract","text":"Guardrails have failed","detail":"AI is repeatedly discussed as a fast-moving system whose ethical 'handbrakes' and cultural 'guardrails' are missing or weak, shifting attention to what steering mechanisms could still constrain it.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6g89el6b9w"},{"id":"fd-mq6g89el0idn","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:07.197Z","type":"abstract","text":"Institutional mediation of choice","detail":"Even where users appear to have model choice, the real dynamics are filtered through institutions, authority structures, education systems, and elite interpreters rather than isolated individual preference.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6g89ell8h5"},{"id":"fd-mq6g89elf58y","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:07.197Z","type":"abstract","text":"From market issue to governance crisis","detail":"Several points recast AI from a commercial product problem into a broader political-governance problem once concentration, unemployment, or mass discontent exceed what markets can absorb.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6g89el033h"},{"id":"fd-mq6g89emhamq","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:07.198Z","type":"abstract","text":"Outpaced control loop","detail":"The discussion repeatedly assumes a mismatch between the speed of AI change and the slower response times of academia, ethics, culture, and public institutions, making adaptation hard.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6g89ell9nx"},{"id":"fd-mq6g8oisv8v9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.788Z","type":"bridge","text":"There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial. \u2194 There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6g8oisdfhf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g8oitrv3m","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.789Z","type":"bridge","text":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal. \u2194 There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6g8oitl4lf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g8oitj46o","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:26.789Z","type":"bridge","text":"When discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes political. \u2194 There is only so much that can be done within the scale or range of the commercial; when discontent becomes large enough, the problem becomes societal or politi\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6g8oith0ue"},{"id":"fd-mq6g9bqg0frb","ts":"2026-06-09T09:40:56.872Z","type":"merge","text":"Rapid Change \u2192 Rapid Change","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto"},{"id":"fd-mq6g9s0tpnp9","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:17.981Z","type":"refine","text":"How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind of thing.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g9st6ylwx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.002Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Ostrom Commons Design Principles","detail":"This is about designing shared norms and governance for a common institutional environment, which fits the idea that commons can be sustained through locally adapted rules and guardrails.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6g9r7sz2wf"},{"id":"fd-mq6g9tj8wnnu","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.940Z","type":"bridge","text":"How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind\u2026 \u2194 How can academia shorten its feedback loop enough to remain useful in fast-moving real-world contexts?","detail":"Both ask how academic institutions can become responsive to fast-moving realities, and your note adds the cultural preconditions that make that speed possible.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6g9tj8cyue"},{"id":"fd-mq6g9tj92n66","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:19.941Z","type":"bridge","text":"How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind\u2026 \u2194 Cultural Guardrails","detail":"The note is essentially about the institutionalization of cultural guardrails, which fits the broader theme of how norms and soft constraints can shape behavior.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6g9tj8f8o9"},{"id":"fd-mq6gam1m3twn","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z","type":"bridge","text":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning. \u2194 Assessment should be designed to drive genuine learning, not just measure it.","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6gam1m68x9"},{"id":"fd-mq6gam1m3dvz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:41:56.890Z","type":"bridge","text":"One has to rethink assessment: assessment can be reframed so that students cannot avoid learning. \u2194 How should assessment be redesigned so it reliably requires and reinforces learning without creating unfair or overly restrictive constraints?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6gam1mg64w"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbfzm7bqc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:35.698Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as concentrated power infrastructure","detail":"Discussion repeatedly treats AI less as a neutral tool market and more as infrastructure controlled by entrenched actors, where seller power, lab dominance, and institutional mediation shape what users can actually do.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzl3efk"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbfzmhf34","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:35.698Z","type":"abstract","text":"Runaway system without brakes","detail":"AI progress is described as a fast-moving process whose normal ethical and academic braking mechanisms have failed, creating urgency and a dangerous mismatch between speed of change and speed of oversight.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzmb0gn"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbfzmlxz4","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:35.698Z","type":"abstract","text":"Authority vacuum and delegated judgment","detail":"Several points assume people and institutions are offloading judgment to AI or to authorities around AI, making deference, trust, and instruction central to how the technology is socially adopted.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzmh4a5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbfzmpmq6","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:35.698Z","type":"abstract","text":"Culture as soft infrastructure","detail":"Culture, ethics, and guardrails are treated as an invisible but load-bearing layer that must be built into institutions and disciplines if society is to steer AI rather than merely react to it.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzm3vja"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbfzmmxz3","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:35.698Z","type":"abstract","text":"Institutional lag versus social disruption","detail":"A recurring model is that AI-driven economic and educational disruption is arriving faster than schools, academia, and politics can adapt, forcing reform under pressure rather than through orderly planning.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzmxi6l"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbpwcbzj6","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:48.540Z","type":"merge","text":"Pedagogy Weakness \u2192 Pedagogy Weakness","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6g6hi1edx5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbweqpc6b","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z","type":"bridge","text":"Cultural guardrails and soft infrastructure can be built into all academic disciplines. \u2194 How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gbweqf9jm"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbweqopwq","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.978Z","type":"bridge","text":"Some disciplines, such as STEM, have poor cultural soil for these measures. \u2194 How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gbweqsg1k"},{"id":"fd-mq6gbwerkfx2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:42:56.979Z","type":"bridge","text":"The question asks how to integrate these supports across disciplines. \u2194 How can cultural guardrails and \"soft infrastructure\" be built into all academic disciplines? Some disciplines, like STEM, have poor cultural soil for this kind\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gbwertyf8"},{"id":"fd-mq6genh6wf14","ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z","type":"abstract","text":"governance lag","detail":"Again and again the discussion assumes that technical and market change are moving faster than the institutions meant to steer them, leaving ethics, academia, and politics in a reactive posture.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6genh6ixke","ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z","type":"abstract","text":"power asymmetry","detail":"A recurring model is that AI systems and their producers hold disproportionate leverage over users and publics, whether in markets, authority relations, or lab entrenchment.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6genh6l39q"},{"id":"fd-mq6genh60ek0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z","type":"abstract","text":"guardrails as infrastructure","detail":"Ethics, culture, and pedagogy are treated less as optional beliefs than as supporting infrastructure that can constrain, channel, and course-correct AI's social effects.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6genh6jq5q"},{"id":"fd-mq6genh6xoq1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z","type":"abstract","text":"containment failure","detail":"The conversation repeatedly imagines AI as a force escaping prior limits\u2014ethical handbrakes gone, commercial bounds exceeded, and in the extreme an AGI that consumes rather than serves humans.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6genh66jel","ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z","type":"abstract","text":"plural adoption over moral consensus","detail":"Several points assume that uptake will be driven by heterogeneous preferences, institutional context, and secular reception rather than by shared ethical agreement about AI.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6genh64vpl"},{"id":"fd-mq6gfxyn34ex","ts":"2026-06-09T09:46:05.615Z","type":"merge","text":"Academic Pace \u2192 Rapid Change","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6g5r4xjdto"},{"id":"fd-mq6gjcr2frob","ts":"2026-06-09T09:48:44.750Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as authority surrogate","detail":"Across discussion of deference, model choice, and human-AI interaction, AI is treated less as a neutral tool than as an actor people consult for direction, legitimacy, or judgment.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gjcr2dbxz"},{"id":"fd-mq6gjcr3my9f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:48:44.751Z","type":"abstract","text":"Guardrails as social infrastructure","detail":"Ethics, culture, and pedagogy are framed as the soft rails, soil, or handbrakes that keep AI development and use aligned, and the concern is that these supports are weak or absent.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gjcr232vf"},{"id":"fd-mq6gjcr3b7z1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:48:44.751Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI economy as concentrated power","detail":"Multiple points assume a structural imbalance in which frontier labs and vendors hold durable leverage while consumers, universities, and ordinary workers have limited ability to shape outcomes.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gjcr3gzms"},{"id":"fd-mq6gjcr3n9cj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:48:44.751Z","type":"abstract","text":"Technological disruption as regime change","detail":"The conversation repeatedly casts AI not as incremental innovation but as a civilizational rupture that can reorder labor markets, politics, cultural norms, and even the human position relative to machines.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gjcr3g67m"},{"id":"fd-mq6gkv0rp0rc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:55.083Z","type":"refine","text":"It is not about substituting people; it is about how to educate people to coexist with AI.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gkr5h1wah"},{"id":"fd-mq6gkv0rcih2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:55.083Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 AI Coexistence","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6gkv0ru78w"},{"id":"fd-mq6gkw3j89y5","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:56.479Z","type":"bridge","text":"It is not about substituting people; it is about how to educate people to coexist with AI. \u2194 How will education change with AI?","detail":"Both frame AI as a prompt to rethink education, but this note sharpens that into preparing people to live alongside AI rather than merely updating curricula.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6gkw3jsn0m"},{"id":"fd-mq6gkw3js3ws","ts":"2026-06-09T09:49:56.479Z","type":"bridge","text":"It is not about substituting people; it is about how to educate people to coexist with AI. \u2194 How can we help workers and institutions adapt to rapid change without causing unnecessary disruption?","detail":"Coexisting with AI is a specific form of adaptation to rapid change, focusing the broader resilience question on human training and institutions.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6gkw3ja6ww"},{"id":"fd-mq6gkyylwx89","ts":"2026-06-09T09:50:00.189Z","type":"merge","text":"AI Coexistence \u2192 AI Coexistence","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fbnyu6xum"},{"id":"fd-mq6gla8jalwz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:50:14.803Z","type":"merge","text":"AGI Human Risk \u2192 AI Coexistence","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fbnyu6xum"},{"id":"fd-mq6gla8ji4cd","ts":"2026-06-09T09:50:14.803Z","type":"merge","text":"Assessment Reform \u2192 Assessment Reform","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6g6hi1edx5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gn9efcu4w","ts":"2026-06-09T09:51:47.031Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as infrastructure, not just a product","detail":"The discussion repeatedly treats AI as something embedded in institutions, education, culture, and politics, so its effects cannot be understood purely as consumer choice or market exchange.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gn9efnlki","ts":"2026-06-09T09:51:47.031Z","type":"abstract","text":"Arms-race speed versus institutional lag","detail":"A recurring contrast pits rapid AI change and urgent real-world impacts against slower-moving academia, ethics, and governance systems that struggle to stay in the feedback loop.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efv460"},{"id":"fd-mq6gn9efrz47","ts":"2026-06-09T09:51:47.031Z","type":"abstract","text":"Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"Instead of a simple substitution story, the conversation keeps returning to how humans, institutions, and education must adapt to live with AI under conditions of possible displacement and asymmetric power.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efsycu"},{"id":"fd-mq6go0qdnm7c","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:22.453Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 AI Regulation","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6go0qds0al"},{"id":"fd-mq6go1ogzngc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.680Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Outside View / Inside View","detail":"This is a forecasting question about where a regulatory landscape is heading, so the best heuristic is to start from broader reference classes and then adjust with EU/UK-specific mechanism.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6go00aw4x6"},{"id":"fd-mq6go1vzz7mr","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.951Z","type":"bridge","text":"Where are the EU and UK heading in terms of AI regulation? \u2194 AI Regulation","detail":"The question is directly about AI regulation, making it a natural anchor for the EU/UK policy direction discussion.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6go1vzh8nv"},{"id":"fd-mq6go1vz0ux2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:23.951Z","type":"bridge","text":"Where are the EU and UK heading in terms of AI regulation? \u2194 Societal Political Shift","detail":"EU/UK regulation often shifts from technical rulemaking into broader societal and political contestation once AI harms or public concern become large enough.","head":"causes","ref":"b-mq6go1vzbkjc"},{"id":"fd-mq6godq7ibk2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:52:39.295Z","type":"merge","text":"AI Lab Entrenchment \u2192 AI Coexistence","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fbnyu6xum"},{"id":"fd-mq6gp75smvtw","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:17.440Z","type":"refine","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"fd-mq6gp75sd7ot","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:17.440Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Regulation and Growth","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6gp75spy94"},{"id":"fd-mq6gp8huqx3c","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:19.170Z","type":"bridge","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth. \u2194 Where are the EU and UK heading in terms of AI regulation?","detail":"Both point to regulation as a live policy question, but the new note adds the less obvious claim that well-designed regulation can be growth-enabling rather than just restrictive.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6gp8huafwe"},{"id":"fd-mq6gp8huma0c","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:19.170Z","type":"bridge","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth. \u2194 Regulation and Growth","detail":"This directly deepens the theme that regulation and growth are not opposites, and suggests a more nuanced pro-growth role for regulation.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6gp8hue2t3"},{"id":"fd-mq6gpb6ty3sj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.661Z","type":"factcheck","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth.","detail":"This is broadly defensible: regulation can reduce harmful uncertainty, build trust, standardise markets, and curb anti-competitive behavior, all of which can support growth. But regulation can also slow entry, raise compliance costs, and protect incumbents, so its effect depends heavily on design and context.","head":"needs-nuance","ref":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"fd-mq6gpb6tnr2t","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.661Z","type":"boundary","text":"Boundary \u00b7 true, but only when regulation is predictable, proportionate, enforceable, and aligned with market failures or coordination problems; it breaks when rules are overly burdensome, poorly targeted, or captured by incumbents.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"fd-mq6gpb6us2v3","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:22.662Z","type":"principle","text":"Principle \u00b7 Institutional quality matters more than the simple presence or absence of regulation: good rules can create the conditions for innovation and scale, while bad rules can suppress them.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gp678orat"},{"id":"fd-mq6gpnqnkvzc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z","type":"bridge","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth. \u2194 Policy should balance constraints with enabling conditions for growth","detail":"implied value","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6gpnqnsylb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gpnqnlsli","ts":"2026-06-09T09:53:38.927Z","type":"bridge","text":"The simple picture that regulation stifles growth is wrong; there is more to it, and regulation can enable growth. \u2194 What kinds of regulation most effectively support growth rather than hinder it?","detail":"question raised","head":"abduced","ref":"b-mq6gpnqnqxim"},{"id":"fd-mq6gqgyrqjyw","ts":"2026-06-09T09:54:16.803Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as an entrenched sovereign","detail":"AI systems and frontier labs are repeatedly discussed as entities with concentrated power and authority that users, institutions, and even governments must navigate rather than simply control.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyrtre5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gqgyrbqbw","ts":"2026-06-09T09:54:16.803Z","type":"abstract","text":"Guardrails and handbrakes","detail":"Ethics, culture, and regulation are framed as braking and steering mechanisms needed to keep rapid technological change aligned with human values and social stability.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyrn4in"},{"id":"fd-mq6gqgyri4qi","ts":"2026-06-09T09:54:16.803Z","type":"abstract","text":"Temporal mismatch in governance","detail":"A recurring model is that social institutions like academia, education, and policy operate on slower cycles than AI development, creating a lagged feedback problem.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyrz96q"},{"id":"fd-mq6gqgyso1x2","ts":"2026-06-09T09:54:16.804Z","type":"abstract","text":"From market question to societal settlement","detail":"The discussion repeatedly shifts from consumer choice and commercial competition to the idea that AI's real effects are resolved at the level of politics, culture, and social order.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyri5g4"},{"id":"fd-mq6gqgysmpno","ts":"2026-06-09T09:54:16.804Z","type":"abstract","text":"Education as adaptation infrastructure","detail":"Schooling and assessment are treated less as content delivery and more as society's mechanism for training humans to remain capable, accountable, and able to coexist with AI.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gqgysnj8g"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtpbbd2ev","ts":"2026-06-09T09:56:47.591Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as an entrenched infrastructure layer","detail":"AI is treated less like a normal product and more like a foundational system run by actors that are hard to dislodge, shaping user choice, institutional dependence, and the scope for regulation.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbb05kz"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtpbb27mr","ts":"2026-06-09T09:56:47.591Z","type":"abstract","text":"Runaway vehicle without brakes","detail":"The discussion repeatedly casts AI change as fast-moving and difficult to steer, with ethical handbrakes removed and slower institutions unable to stay in the feedback loop.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbbx3zu"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtpbbppng","ts":"2026-06-09T09:56:47.591Z","type":"abstract","text":"Cultural governance as soft infrastructure","detail":"Many points assume that norms, pedagogy, discipline-specific culture, and guardrails are governance mechanisms as important as formal law for steering AI adoption and coexistence.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbbactz"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtpbciy12","ts":"2026-06-09T09:56:47.592Z","type":"abstract","text":"Economic disruption spilling into political backlash","detail":"The conversation links labor-market shock and commercial concentration to a broader societal tipping point where the issue stops being merely economic and becomes political and regulatory.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbcdjwb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtvjb3mys","ts":"2026-06-09T09:56:55.655Z","type":"merge","text":"Secular Reception \u2192 AI Coexistence","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fbnyu6xum"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtzngx9vi","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.988Z","type":"merge","text":"AI as sovereign authority, AI as authority surrogate \u2192 AI as sovereign authority","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyrtre5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhk0og","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails and handbrakes, Runaway system without brakes, Runaway vehicle without brakes, Safety systems as vanished guardrails \u2192 Safety systems as vanished guardrails","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhc9xh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"Institutional lag versus social disruption, Arms-race speed versus institutional lag, Institutional lag, Temporal mismatch in governance \u2192 Institutional lag","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznh4lcx","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"From market issue to political rupture, From market issue to governance crisis \u2192 From market issue to governance crisis","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbcdjwb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhf3tl","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"Authority vacuum and delegated judgment \u2192 Institutional mediation of choice","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6g89ell8h5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhtmpz","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"AI economy as concentrated power \u2192 AI as concentrated power infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzl3efk"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhmq5h","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"Cultural governance as soft infrastructure \u2192 Culture as soft infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzm3vja"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhngt1","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails as social infrastructure \u2192 Guardrails as social infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6jq5q"},{"id":"fd-mq6gtznhfx5z","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:00.989Z","type":"merge","text":"AI as an entrenched infrastructure layer \u2192 AI as infrastructure, not just a product","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gutwna8fh","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:40.199Z","type":"merge","text":"Assessment Reform \u2192 Model Preferences","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6f026scvpu"},{"id":"fd-mq6guv8ynfey","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:41.938Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails have failed \u2192 Guardrails have failed","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6guv8yniup","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:41.938Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails as social infrastructure \u2192 Guardrails as social infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gbfzm3vja"},{"id":"fd-mq6guv8yfsq8","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:41.938Z","type":"merge","text":"AI as concentrated power infrastructure \u2192 AI as infrastructure, not just a product","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6guv8yahad","ts":"2026-06-09T09:57:41.938Z","type":"merge","text":"From market question to societal settlement \u2192 From market question to societal settlement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbcdjwb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gvrq2rvob","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:24.026Z","type":"refine","text":"The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking about what comes next?","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd"},{"id":"fd-mq6gvrq2iity","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:24.026Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Future After Revolution","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6gvrq20h0p"},{"id":"fd-mq6gvsr0ccqu","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.356Z","type":"heuristic","text":"Heuristic \u00b7 Outside View / Inside View","detail":"The note is asking us to generalize from a historical pattern of revolutions and then adjust with a forward-looking specific forecast, which fits starting from the reference class and then considering case-specific next steps.","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gvqrezmvd"},{"id":"fd-mq6gvssw56h7","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.424Z","type":"bridge","text":"The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking a\u2026 \u2194 Address pressing current problems now, not only future risks.","detail":"Both suggest the revolution\u2019s present force can distract from urgent attention to the near-term problems that still need action now.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6gvssw17gk"},{"id":"fd-mq6gvsswkj8f","ts":"2026-06-09T09:58:25.424Z","type":"bridge","text":"The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking a\u2026 \u2194 Future After Revolution","detail":"The note directly aligns with the theme of thinking beyond the revolution itself toward what kind of post-revolution future should be prepared for.","head":"relates","ref":"b-mq6gvsswtkhd"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwjxlbkrb","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:00.585Z","type":"refine","text":"Pluralism is good and worthwhile for healthy ecosystems, but to achieve that we need to act now.","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"n-mq6gwj3617yi"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwjxlbw6h","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:00.585Z","type":"theme","text":"New theme \u00b7 Pluralism","detail":"","head":null,"ref":"t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwl70p2y0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:02.220Z","type":"bridge","text":"Pluralism is good and worthwhile for healthy ecosystems, but to achieve that we need to act now. \u2194 Systemic stability matters more than any single lab\u2019s fate.","detail":"Pluralism and ecosystem health both point to the same systemic-stability concern: diversity is valuable precisely because it makes the system less brittle.","head":"tension","ref":"b-mq6gwl70n3xj"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwl707qgp","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:02.220Z","type":"bridge","text":"Pluralism is good and worthwhile for healthy ecosystems, but to achieve that we need to act now. \u2194 Address pressing current problems now, not only future risks.","detail":"The call to act now mirrors the urgency in prioritizing pressing current problems rather than treating future risks as the only reason to move.","head":"echoes","ref":"b-mq6gwl70mbj8"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwn3a71wv","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:04.678Z","type":"merge","text":"Institutional mediation of choice \u2192 Institutional lag","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwn3a0rop","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:04.678Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails as social infrastructure \u2192 Guardrails as social infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwx4nr2zm","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:17.687Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as infrastructure, not just product","detail":"The discussion repeatedly treats AI as embedded in institutions, education, regulation, and culture, so the key question is not mere adoption but how whole systems are organized around it.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gwx4nkslu"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwx4nivse","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:17.687Z","type":"abstract","text":"Guardrails as soft governance","detail":"When formal control is limited or lagging, ethics, culture, pedagogy, and academic norms are imagined as the steering and braking mechanisms that can keep AI aligned with human values.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gwx4n6lzz"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwx4nt673","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:17.687Z","type":"abstract","text":"Temporal mismatch","detail":"A recurring model is that social, academic, and regulatory response cycles move too slowly relative to AI capability and market change, creating governance and adaptation gaps.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gwx4nvxez"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwx4ov5hg","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:17.688Z","type":"abstract","text":"From market issue to political issue","detail":"Several points assume that AI begins as a commercial and consumer matter but, once power concentrates and displacement spreads, it becomes a question of social legitimacy and collective political response.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gwx4nm6f6"},{"id":"fd-mq6gwx4oq13t","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:17.688Z","type":"abstract","text":"Ecosystem health","detail":"Pluralism, coexistence, education, and regulation are discussed as conditions for maintaining a resilient ecosystem rather than maximizing a single actor's dominance or a single metric of growth.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gwx4o4i3r"},{"id":"fd-mq6gx8gjrzie","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:32.371Z","type":"merge","text":"Regulation and Growth \u2192 AI Regulation","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6go0qds0al"},{"id":"fd-mq6gx9nyrbe6","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:33.934Z","type":"merge","text":"AI as infrastructure, not just product \u2192 AI as infrastructure, not just a product","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gx9nzbdeg","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:33.935Z","type":"merge","text":"From market issue to political issue \u2192 From market question to societal settlement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbcdjwb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gx9nzijyk","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:33.935Z","type":"merge","text":"Outpaced control loop \u2192 Institutional lag","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6gx9nzm5l0","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:33.935Z","type":"merge","text":"Temporal mismatch \u2192 Temporal mismatch","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gqgyrtre5"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxdlnj14q","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","type":"bridge","text":"A technology revolution can seem powerful in the moment. \u2194 The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking a\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gxdln9kvv"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxdlnmwsn","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","type":"bridge","text":"Technology revolutions are often later overshadowed. \u2194 The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking a\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gxdln2o78"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxdlno170","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:39.035Z","type":"bridge","text":"We should consider what comes next after a technology revolution. \u2194 The common character of a technology revolution is that it always seems powerful in the moment, but it gets overshadowed; to what extent should we be thinking a\u2026","detail":"proposition drawn from a longer point","head":"instance-of","ref":"b-mq6gxdlnzl8b"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxmvuh5tg","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:51.066Z","type":"merge","text":"Authority Deference \u2192 Model Preferences","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6f026scvpu"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxmvvofaj","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:51.067Z","type":"merge","text":"AI Regulation \u2192 AI Regulation","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fdx4vnsd2"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxmvvqg54","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:51.067Z","type":"merge","text":"Future After Revolution \u2192 Societal Political Shift","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fuxy57gve"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxnq3npjc","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:52.155Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails as soft governance \u2192 Guardrails as social infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxr89tl7l","ts":"2026-06-09T09:59:56.697Z","type":"merge","text":"Temporal mismatch \u2192 Temporal mismatch","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxvp8tyew","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:02.492Z","type":"merge","text":"Technological disruption as regime change \u2192 Technological disruption as regime change","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gxvp8v2mn","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:02.492Z","type":"merge","text":"Education as adaptation infrastructure \u2192 Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efsycu"},{"id":"fd-mq6gy183j0g4","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:09.651Z","type":"merge","text":"Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement \u2192 Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gtpbcdjwb"},{"id":"fd-mq6gy3307uib","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:12.060Z","type":"merge","text":"Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement \u2192 Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gy653hzeq","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:16.023Z","type":"merge","text":"Ecosystem health \u2192 Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gy95x3jbd","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:19.941Z","type":"merge","text":"AI Coexistence \u2192 Model Preferences","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6f026scvpu"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyd1d1v3y","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:24.961Z","type":"merge","text":"plural adoption over moral consensus \u2192 Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyzn26x04","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.254Z","type":"abstract","text":"AI as infrastructure, not just a product","detail":"Discussion repeatedly treats AI as a system that reshapes institutions like education, labor markets, and politics, so the key question is how society is reorganized around it rather than simply whether people buy or use it.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gyzn2uvgf"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyzn2g54e","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.254Z","type":"abstract","text":"Guardrails as soft infrastructure","detail":"Ethics, culture, pedagogy, and academic norms are framed as an invisible safety system whose erosion leaves AI development and adoption without brakes or course-correction capacity.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6gyzn2ihf0"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyzn3iji7","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.255Z","type":"abstract","text":"Temporal mismatch / racing the feedback loop","detail":"A recurring model is that social, academic, and regulatory institutions move too slowly relative to AI change, creating governance and adaptation failures because correction arrives after the system has already shifted.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gyzn2jp6i"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyzn3xhic","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.255Z","type":"abstract","text":"Authority vacuum and delegated judgment","detail":"Several points assume people and institutions are offloading judgment to AI or to elites managing AI, making the core issue one of who gets to decide and how deference is structured.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gyzn3zzba"},{"id":"fd-mq6gyzn33qd0","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.255Z","type":"abstract","text":"Political economy beyond the market","detail":"The conversation repeatedly shifts from consumer choice and firm competition to the idea that once concentration, unemployment, or discontent get large enough, AI becomes a societal governance problem rather than a normal commercial one.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6gyzn3pzz7"},{"id":"fd-mq6gz3cqx2l4","ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:59.066Z","type":"merge","text":"Mass Unemployment \u2192 Mass Unemployment","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"t-mq6fuxy57gve"},{"id":"fd-mq6gz47svkx4","ts":"2026-06-09T10:01:00.184Z","type":"merge","text":"Temporal mismatch / racing the feedback loop \u2192 Temporal mismatch","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh5seos"},{"id":"fd-mq6gz47sibno","ts":"2026-06-09T10:01:00.184Z","type":"merge","text":"Guardrails as soft infrastructure \u2192 Guardrails as infrastructure","detail":"","head":"merged","ref":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n"},{"id":"fd-mq6h8ptyo7hn","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:28.102Z","type":"paper","text":"Report compiled \u2014 0 verified citations across 24 notes","detail":"/api/paper?file=paper-2026-06-09-10-08-20%2Fpaper-2026-06-09-10-08-20.pdf","head":"report","ref":null},{"id":"fd-mq6h8xlfgldm","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z","type":"abstract","text":"ecosystem health","detail":"AI is repeatedly discussed less as a single product market than as an ecosystem whose health depends on diversity, institutional context, and rules that shape whether choice and competition are real.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6h8xlfvi6g"},{"id":"fd-mq6h8xlf7tf8","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z","type":"abstract","text":"guardrails and handbrakes","detail":"Ethics, culture, and education are framed as the braking and steering mechanisms missing from rapid AI deployment, with 'soft infrastructure' needed to keep technical power aligned with human values.","head":"metaphor","ref":"fr-mq6h8xlf37y6"},{"id":"fd-mq6h8xlfhiae","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z","type":"abstract","text":"authority vacuum","detail":"A recurring model is that people and institutions defer to AI as an authority while traditional sources of guidance lag, making governance and norm-setting a problem of who gets to tell whom what to do.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6h8xlfnobt"},{"id":"fd-mq6h8xlf9plz","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z","type":"abstract","text":"pace mismatch","detail":"The discussion repeatedly assumes a structural mismatch between the speed of AI change and the slower response times of academia, culture, labor markets, and policy, creating weak feedback loops and delayed course correction.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6h8xlfqsnh"},{"id":"fd-mq6h8xlf4mu8","ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z","type":"abstract","text":"from commercial problem to political problem","detail":"Several points treat AI impacts as crossing a threshold where market choices and firm-level responses stop being sufficient and the issue becomes one of collective governance, social stability, and public power.","head":"frame","ref":"fr-mq6h8xlfdo78"}],"frames":[{"id":"fr-mq6genh5seos","name":"Temporal mismatch","frameKind":"frame","gist":"AI is repeatedly treated less as a passive tool and more as a commanding authority whose outputs people defer to, whose providers hold asymmetric power, and whose role can shape human behavior without resolving metaphysical questions about minds.","themeIds":["t-mq6fwwdoma3i","t-mq6g5r4xjdto","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6g6hi1edx5","t-mq6g7q2dy8tk","t-mq6fu0d21tjs","t-mq6go0qds0al","t-mq6f026scvpu","t-mq6f4nodk6e8","t-mq6faexfmh3u","t-mq6fbnyu6xum","t-mq6g6apehhpm","t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6gp75spy94"],"ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.369Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6genh6l39q","name":"power asymmetry","frameKind":"frame","gist":"A recurring model is that AI systems and their producers hold disproportionate leverage over users and publics, whether in markets, authority relations, or lab entrenchment.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6f4nodk6e8","t-mq6g4j1hci6z","t-mq6fbnyu6xum"],"ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6genh6xl1n","name":"Guardrails as infrastructure","frameKind":"metaphor","gist":"Ethics, culture, and academic norms are described as braking or steering mechanisms that have weakened or disappeared, creating urgency around rebuilding soft constraints before technical and social change outruns them.","themeIds":["t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6fht58xkl8","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6g5r4xjdto","t-mq6fu0d21tjs","t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6go0qds0al","t-mq6gp75spy94","t-mq6fwwdoma3i","t-mq6g7q2dy8tk","t-mq6g6hi1edx5","t-mq6g7a4c8ajl","t-mq6fbnyu6xum","t-mq6f4nodk6e8","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T09:45:05.370Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6gn9efwwff","name":"Coexistence as adaptation rather than replacement","frameKind":"frame","gist":"Several points assume that AI disruption starts as a commercial or consumer problem but, once powerlessness and displacement scale up, it exits the market frame and becomes a matter of mass politics, backlash, and social order.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6f026scvpu","t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6g6hi1edx5","t-mq6fbnyu6xum","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6go0qds0al","t-mq6gp75spy94","t-mq6g4j1hci6z","t-mq6fu0d21tjs","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2","t-mq6fht58xkl8","t-mq6g5r4xjdto","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6gvrq20h0p","t-mq6faexfmh3u"],"ts":"2026-06-09T09:51:47.031Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6gyzn2uvgf","name":"AI as infrastructure, not just a product","frameKind":"metaphor","gist":"Discussion repeatedly treats AI as a system that reshapes institutions like education, labor markets, and politics, so the key question is how society is reorganized around it rather than simply whether people buy or use it.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6fu0d21tjs","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6g5r4xjdto","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.254Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6gyzn3zzba","name":"Authority vacuum and delegated judgment","frameKind":"frame","gist":"Several points assume people and institutions are offloading judgment to AI or to elites managing AI, making the core issue one of who gets to decide and how deference is structured.","themeIds":["t-mq6f026scvpu","t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.255Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6gyzn3pzz7","name":"Political economy beyond the market","frameKind":"frame","gist":"The conversation repeatedly shifts from consumer choice and firm competition to the idea that once concentration, unemployment, or discontent get large enough, AI becomes a societal governance problem rather than a normal commercial one.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6fu0d21tjs","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:00:54.255Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6h8xlfvi6g","name":"ecosystem health","frameKind":"metaphor","gist":"AI is repeatedly discussed less as a single product market than as an ecosystem whose health depends on diversity, institutional context, and rules that shape whether choice and competition are real.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6f026scvpu","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6h8xlf37y6","name":"guardrails and handbrakes","frameKind":"metaphor","gist":"Ethics, culture, and education are framed as the braking and steering mechanisms missing from rapid AI deployment, with 'soft infrastructure' needed to keep technical power aligned with human values.","themeIds":["t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6g5r4xjdto"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6h8xlfnobt","name":"authority vacuum","frameKind":"frame","gist":"A recurring model is that people and institutions defer to AI as an authority while traditional sources of guidance lag, making governance and norm-setting a problem of who gets to tell whom what to do.","themeIds":["t-mq6f026scvpu","t-mq6fq93e7lei","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6h8xlfqsnh","name":"pace mismatch","frameKind":"frame","gist":"The discussion repeatedly assumes a structural mismatch between the speed of AI change and the slower response times of academia, culture, labor markets, and policy, creating weak feedback loops and delayed course correction.","themeIds":["t-mq6g5r4xjdto","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6fq93e7lei"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z"},{"id":"fr-mq6h8xlfdo78","name":"from commercial problem to political problem","frameKind":"frame","gist":"Several points treat AI impacts as crossing a threshold where market choices and firm-level responses stop being sufficient and the issue becomes one of collective governance, social stability, and public power.","themeIds":["t-mq6ezhokg1b9","t-mq6fuxy57gve","t-mq6fdx4vnsd2","t-mq6gwjxlcvi2"],"ts":"2026-06-09T10:08:38.163Z"}]};